  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"ahri","win":["Skill","Skill","Ahri","Ahri","Malzahar","Ahri","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ahri's spike, not yours: with Q (Orb of Deception), W (Fox-Fire) and E (Charm) online she out-trades you and can Charm-combo you off the wave, so respect her all-in and only shove."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R (Nether Grasp) flips the lane: if she steps up to Charm you and misses, you point-and-click suppress her, drop full E (Malefic Visions) plus voidlings and delete her before ult mobility helps."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After Ludens/Blackfire she buys R (Spirit Rush) dashes for waveclear and roam tempo; her three dashes let her dodge your Q and disengage your R range, tilting the lane back to her."},{"when":"Late","text":"Skill scales even: you have a permanent push and a hard single-target lock for her, she has burst and roam speed, so most late 5v5s come down to whether you ult her or her frontline."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove with E+W and force her to farm under tower where your R threat is safest","Hold R for her Charm whiff, then suppress-combo her instantly","Push before recall so she can't freely roam bot with Spirit Rush"],"foe":["Land Charm to set up a Q-Fox-Fire burst before your R comes up","Use Spirit Rush to dodge your Q and reposition out of R range","Roam with her ult tempo while you're stuck clearing the wave"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even: you both trade with basics and E ticks, but neither has a kill threat yet, so match her push and last-hit safely.","mid":"Levels 3-5 belong to Ahri because Charm plus Fox-Fire out-trades you and threatens an all-in you can't answer until 6, so give ground and shove waves instead of fighting.","late":"At 6 your Nether Grasp is the great equalizer against a whiffed Charm, but once she has Spirit Rush and items her dashes let her poke, dodge, and roam around you, keeping the matchup a coinflip near 50%.","whys":["Level 1 is even because both of you only have single abilities and no committal kill pattern.","Level 2 stays skill-matched as her second ability adds trade damage but still no lockdown on you.","Level 3 favors Ahri once Charm-Fox-Fire-Orb comes online and out-trades your point-blank kit.","Levels 4-5 favor Ahri because her Charm all-in threatens you and you have no R answer yet.","Level 6 favors Malzahar since Nether Grasp punishes any stepped-up Charm whiff with a suppress kill.","First item favors Ahri as Spirit Rush dashes let her dodge Q/R and control range.","2+ items even out because your lockdown and her mobility/roam cancel to a near-coinflip."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"akali","win":["Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Akali","Akali"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is your lane: you shove with E (Malefic Visions) and W (Void Swarm) faster than she clears, keeping her pinned under tower and denying the roam windows Akali lives on."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R (Nether Grasp) hard-counters her all-in: when she Shroud-dashes onto you, suppress her mid-combo and she can't Q-E-R you back, turning her engage into her death."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Akali's power turns on here: with Gunblade/Rift-item plus levels her R (Perfect Execution) dashes let her wait out your ult and one-shot you the moment R is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Akali outscales: her repeated Shroud resets and two R dashes let her pick the moment your Nether Grasp is on cooldown, so you must play with the team and a QSS-style out."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove every wave with E+W to keep her farming under tower","Save R for her Shroud engage and suppress her mid-combo","Build early Zhonya/tenacity so her post-6 all-in isn't lethal"],"foe":["Wait out your R cooldown before committing her all-in","Use Shroud to break your Q line and dodge the suppress","Roam or reset onto you the moment Nether Grasp is down"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are yours: your E-W push out-paces her weak early clear and chunks her if she tries to melee last-hit into your minions.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay firmly Malzahar-favoured because your permanent shove denies her roams and your Nether Grasp is a point-and-click answer to any Shroud all-in she attempts.","late":"Once Akali has items and both R charges she can bait your suppress and burst you when it's down, so the matchup flips to her after first item unless you itemize a cleanse and fight beside your team.","whys":["Level 1 favors Malzahar as your ranged E-W poke beats her melee last-hitting.","Level 2 favors Malzahar because your push and DoT keep her from safely trading.","Level 3 favors Malzahar since you out-shove her clear and lock her under tower.","Levels 4-5 favor Malzahar with your wave control denying her roam tempo.","Level 6 favors Malzahar because Nether Grasp point-blank counters her Shroud engage.","First item favors Akali as her R dashes and burst let her wait out and punish your ult.","2+ items favor Akali since resets and double R let her strike when your suppress is down."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"akshan","win":["Skill","Akshan","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Akshan spikes here: his Q (Avengerang) boomerang poke and E (Heroic Swing) grapple off terrain let him dance in and out, and his passive shields punish you if you walk up to shove, so play safe and farm from range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R (Nether Grasp) is the answer to his mobility: when he E-swings in to burst you, suppress him out of the swing and he can't reposition, flipping his aggression into a kill for you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You out-scale his lane threat: your E-W permanent push pins him and he can't roam-revive teammates without giving up farm, while your suppress remains a hard stop on his engage."},{"when":"Late","text":"Malzahar stays ahead: Akshan needs to swing in to deal damage, and every swing is a free suppress target for your R, so as long as you hold ult for him you win the sidelane and the 5v5 pick."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely from max range and avoid his Q boomerang return hit","Hold R for his E (Heroic Swing) engage and suppress him out of it","Shove with E+W to deny his roams and camp-revive plays"],"foe":["Poke you down with Avengerang and passive-shielded trades before 6","Swing in and burst before your Nether Grasp is available","Roam to revive teammates and snowball off your shoved wave"]},"early":"Level 1 is even, but at Level 2 Akshan pulls ahead as his boomerang poke and grapple mobility let him harass you while dodging your Q line.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay a skill matchup: he can poke and reposition, but if you respect his swing timing and farm safely you reach 6 healthy, where the lane tilts hard toward you.","late":"From Level 6 onward Malzahar controls the matchup because every Heroic Swing is a point-and-click suppress target, and your permanent push denies the roams Akshan needs to snowball.","whys":["Level 1 is even with both champs just last-hitting and no kill pressure.","Level 2 favors Akshan as his boomerang poke and grapple out-harass you.","Level 3 is skill-matched: his poke is real but your farm-safe play holds even.","Levels 4-5 stay even as you trade waveclear for his poke without a kill threat either way.","Level 6 favors Malzahar because Nether Grasp suppresses him out of his Heroic Swing engage.","First item favors Malzahar as your push pins him and denies his revive roams.","2+ items favor Malzahar since every swing-in feeds your suppress in fights and sidelane."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"anivia","win":["Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Anivia","Anivia"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You own this window: before Anivia has her ult and mana she clears slowly, so shove with E (Malefic Visions) and W (Void Swarm), pin her under tower and deny her the CS she needs to come online."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R (Nether Grasp) beats her defensively: if she Q (Flash Frost) stuns and steps up, suppress her before the R-Q-E combo lands, and her egg passive means she still can't punish you back cleanly."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Anivia flips it: with Rylai's/Blackfire plus mana items her R (Glacial Storm) plus E (Frostbite) gives her a wall of unavoidable AoE that out-waveclears you and zones you off farm."},{"when":"Late","text":"Anivia out-scales: her R zone erases your voidlings and E-DoT push, and her egg lets her survive your suppress, so you must catch her Flash-Frost cooldown or fight around her with the team."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove hard levels 3-5 before her Glacial Storm and mana come online","Hold R for her Flash Frost step-up and suppress her out of the combo","Force fights while she's low mana and her egg is on cooldown"],"foe":["Reach 6 and mana items so Glacial Storm zones your voidlings","Wall you with Q (Flash Frost) to set up guaranteed Frostbite burst","Use her egg passive to survive your suppress and out-scale you"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even: Anivia's early clear is clunky and you both just farm, so match her CS and don't over-extend into a Flash Frost.","mid":"Levels 3-5 are yours because you out-shove her weak pre-ult clear, keep her starved under tower, and your Nether Grasp punishes any step-up she makes.","late":"Once Anivia hits 6 with mana items her Glacial Storm plus Frostbite wall out-clears your push and zones you off farm, and her egg blunts your suppress, so the matchup tilts to her into the late game.","whys":["Level 1 is even as both champs farm with no early kill threat.","Level 2 stays even because Anivia's clunky clear doesn't out-trade you yet.","Level 3 favors Malzahar since your E-W shove out-paces her slow pre-ult clear.","Levels 4-5 favor Malzahar as you starve her under tower before Glacial Storm.","Level 6 favors Malzahar because Nether Grasp suppresses her out of any Flash-Frost step-up.","First item favors Anivia once Glacial Storm plus mana zones your voidlings and farm.","2+ items favor Anivia as her R wall out-clears you and her egg survives your ult."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"annie","win":["Skill","Skill","Annie","Annie","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Annie's spike: with a Pyromania stun charged she can Q (Disintegrate) or W (Incinerate) you for a huge chunk, so watch her passive stacks and never walk into stun range to shove."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R (Nether Grasp) out-ranges and out-locks her Tibbers combo: if she Flash-W-R engages, you can suppress her first, or if she's charged, bait the stun then ult her once it's spent."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You pull ahead: your E-W permanent push pins her under tower and out-clears her mana-hungry early, and past 6 your suppress trades one-for-one against her single burst window."},{"when":"Late","text":"Malzahar stays ahead in lane: Annie is a one-shot-or-nothing burst mage, and if you respect her charged stun and hold R for her engage, you win the extended game and the sidelane."}],"wants":{"you":["Track her Pyromania stacks and only shove when her stun isn't charged","Bait the charged stun, then suppress her once Tibbers is committed","Push with E+W to pin her under tower and out-farm her mana pool"],"foe":["Charge Pyromania and Flash-W-R burst you before your suppress lands","Zone you off the wave with charged-stun threat","Roam with Tibbers pressure while you clear the shoved wave"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even: neither of you has a kill threat yet, so last-hit safely and start tracking her passive stun stacks.","mid":"Levels 3-5 favor Annie because a charged Pyromania stun turns her Q or Tibbers into a lethal burst combo you can't answer until 6, so give ground and refuse to walk into stun range.","late":"From Level 6 the lane swings to you: your Nether Grasp out-locks her single engage window, your E-W push pins her under tower, and disciplined stun-tracking lets you out-scale her one-dimensional burst.","whys":["Level 1 is even with both champs farming and no kill pressure.","Level 2 stays even as neither has a committal threat yet.","Level 3 favors Annie once a charged Pyromania stun enables a lethal Q burst.","Levels 4-5 favor Annie because her charged-stun combo zones and threatens you pre-6.","Level 6 favors Malzahar since Nether Grasp out-locks her single Tibbers engage.","First item favors Malzahar as your permanent push pins her and out-farms her mana.","2+ items favor Malzahar because your suppress and scaling beat her one-shot burst window."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"aurelionsol","win":["Malzahar","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Even-to-yours window: Aurelion Sol wants to stack Q (Breath of Light) on you for his passive, but your E-W push forces him to defend the wave, and at 4-5 your shove out-tempos his farm-scaling plan."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R (Nether Grasp) beats his ult setup: if he steps up to channel R (Falling Star / Cosmic Expansion) or stack Q on you, suppress him and cancel the play before his stacks pay off."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You keep the pressure: your permanent E-W push denies the free stacking he needs, so pin him under tower and deny the CS-and-stack economy his whole kit relies on."},{"when":"Late","text":"Skill and scaling even out: with enough stardust his Q-W and expanded ult out-range and out-DPS you, so late fights hinge on whether you land your R on him before his zone control takes over."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove with E+W to deny his free Q stacking and farm","Hold R for his step-up and suppress before he stacks on you","Pressure him under tower so he can't scale on tempo"],"foe":["Stack Q (Breath of Light) safely to grow his passive range and damage","Farm and scale to his item-and-stardust power spike","Zone your voidlings with expanded ult range in the late game"]},"early":"Level 1 favors you as your ranged E-W harass beats his need to walk up and stack Q, then levels 2-3 settle even while he tries to farm safely.","mid":"Levels 4-6 are yours: your permanent push denies the free stacking Aurelion Sol's whole scaling plan depends on, and your Nether Grasp cancels any step-up he makes to stack on you.","late":"Once he has stardust and items his expanded Q-W and ult out-range your push and DPS your voidlings, so the fully-scaled game evens back to a skill matchup decided by landing R on him first.","whys":["Level 1 favors Malzahar as your ranged poke beats his walk-up Q stacking.","Level 2 is even while both farm and he stacks safely.","Level 3 stays even as neither converts a kill threat.","Levels 4-5 favor Malzahar because your push denies his free stacking economy.","Level 6 favors Malzahar since Nether Grasp cancels his step-up and ult setup.","First item favors Malzahar as your pin under tower keeps him off tempo.","2+ items even out once his stardust range and ult zone match your control."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"aurora","win":["Skill","Skill","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora","Aurora"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Aurora's spike: her Q (Twofold Hex) bounce poke and W (Explosive Spirit) hop let her harass you and dodge your Q line, chunking you every time you walk up to shove the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even her ult beats you here: her R (Between Worlds) plus W dashes let her disengage the moment you threaten Nether Grasp, so she can bait your suppress and reposition out of it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Aurora stays ahead: her E (The Weirding) spirit-hop mobility and true-damage passive out-trade your point-blank kit, and she can roam off your shoved wave faster than you punish."},{"when":"Late","text":"Aurora out-scales this lane: her repeated W hops and R banish let her pick when to fight your suppress down, so you must build a cleanse and play tightly with your team to answer her."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely under tower and dodge her Q bounce poke","Bait her W hop before committing Nether Grasp","Build tenacity or cleanse so her post-6 all-in isn't lethal"],"foe":["Poke you with Twofold Hex and stack her true-damage passive","Use W (Explosive Spirit) hops to dodge your Q and R","Roam with her mobility off your shoved wave and fight when your ult is down"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a skill matchup: you both farm and poke, but Aurora's bounce Q already threatens to chip you if you step up carelessly.","mid":"Levels 3-6 belong to Aurora because her Q poke plus W spirit-hops let her out-trade you and dodge your Q, and her mobility means even your Nether Grasp can be baited and side-stepped.","late":"Aurora keeps the edge into items: her hop resets and R banish let her choose the fight while your suppress is down, so respect her all-in, itemize a cleanse, and lean on your team to lock her.","whys":["Level 1 is even as both champs just farm with light poke.","Level 2 stays even before her hop mobility fully out-trades you.","Level 3 favors Aurora once Q poke plus W hops out-trade and dodge your kit.","Levels 4-5 favor Aurora because her mobility harasses you and dodges your Q.","Level 6 favors Aurora as her W and R let her bait and side-step your suppress.","First item favors Aurora since her mobility and true damage out-trade and out-roam you.","2+ items favor Aurora because her resets let her fight when your Nether Grasp is down."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"azir","win":["Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Azir","Azir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once E Malefic Visions is online you out-shove Azir hard; slam E onto the caster minion and let it bounce so the wave crashes into his tower while he is still stacking soldiers, denying his farm and cracking his weak early game open."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"R Nether Grasp is your kill window: Azir has no escape until his soldiers are set, so walk up behind a voidling wall, Q to silence his W-E shuffle, then point-click suppress him for a guaranteed kill or a summoner burn."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is where it flips: Azir's soldier DPS and range come online, he zones you off the wave and answers your all-in with a soldier shurima-shuffle knockback, so respect the spacing and farm safe."},{"when":"Late","text":"Full-uptime soldiers plus his ult wall let Azir kite your immobile combo; only engage with R when his shuffle is down or a teammate has locked him first."}],"wants":{"you":["Hit level 3 fast and perma-shove Azir under tower with E so he misses CS and cannot free-farm to his item spike","Land R Nether Grasp before he has soldiers positioned to peel, ideally with Q silence pre-loading the suppression","Roam on the crashed wave to punish his weak early game on side lanes and set up your jungler"],"foe":["Reach his first item and full soldier count so his DPS and range can zone you off the wave","Bait your R on cooldown, then shurima-shuffle you back with soldiers to disengage","Scale into a teamfight where his wall and soldier zone outrange your single-target lockdown"]},"early":"You are simply the better level 1-2 champion: stronger base stats and Q Call of the Void silence beat Azir's mana-hungry, weak early soldier trades, so hold priority and set up the crash.","mid":"From 3 to 6 you own the lane; E waveclear pins Azir under tower and at 6 your point-click R suppresses an immobile Azir before his soldiers can peel, making this your primary kill and roam window.","late":"Once Azir buys his first item and stabilizes his soldier count the matchup inverts; his range, DPS and ult wall let him kite you, so shift to peeling for your carries and only ult him under lockdown.","whys":["You out-stat and out-trade Azir at level 1 with sturdier bases and a Q silence into his frail early game.","At level 2 you shove first and deny his weak soldier trades, keeping tempo on your side.","Level 3 E waveclear lets you pin Azir under tower and starve his farm before his spike.","Through levels 4-5 you keep the wave crashing and control the lane, holding priority over him.","At 6 your point-click R suppresses immobile Azir before his soldiers can peel, giving you the kill window.","At his first item Azir's soldier DPS and range come online, letting him zone you off the wave.","With two-plus items his ult wall and full soldier uptime kite your immobile combo and outscale you."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"brand","win":["Brand","Brand","Brand","Brand","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Brand owns this window: his W Pillar of Flame poke and passive ambient DoT chunk you every time you step up for CS, and if he lands W into Q Sear on an ablaze target you eat a stun-burst, so farm at max range and lean on your passive shield to soak the ticks."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"The lane flips at 6: Brand is squishy and immobile, so Q to silence his combo, then R Nether Grasp point-click suppresses him through his skillshots for a clean kill before he can pillar you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You out-scale his mana-hungry poke; with your first item you threaten a lethal R all-in every time it is up, forcing him to play back and give you the wave."},{"when":"Late","text":"Reliable point-click suppression plus voidling and passive shield beat Brand's skillshot-reliant burst; in fights, R the Brand to shut his AoE chain down if no one else can reach him."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the level 1-4 poke phase by farming at range and using your passive Void Shield to eat his ambient DoT and W ticks","Hit 6 and land Q into R Nether Grasp to point-click suppress immobile Brand before he combos you","Punish his high mana costs by all-in-ing when his poke has drained him and your R is up"],"foe":["Poke you below half with repeated W Pillar of Flame before you reach your level 6 spike","Land a full W-Q-E ablaze combo to stun-burst you when you step up for CS","Keep the lane long and stay at max range so your point-click R can never connect"]},"early":"Brand hard-bullies you levels 1-2 with W poke and passive burn; do not contest trades, just soak CS at range and trust your shield to blunt the chip damage.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay rough as his sustained W poke and stun combo threaten you at every minion, but the moment you hit 6 the matchup turns: your point-click R suppresses immobile Brand straight through his skillshots.","late":"With items your scaling and lethal R all-in outclass his mana-hungry skillshot poke; play for the pick, silence his combo, and suppress him out of every fight.","whys":["Brand's level 1 W poke and passive ambient DoT chunk you before your shield matters.","At level 2 his stacked W-Q combo out-trades you as you step up for CS.","Through level 3 his AoE clears alongside yours but his range keeps you poked out.","At levels 4-5 his sustained W poke and burst threaten you at every CS attempt.","At 6 your point-click R suppresses immobile Brand straight through his skillshots for the kill.","With your first item you out-scale his mana costs and threaten a lethal R all-in whenever it is up.","With two-plus items your reliable point-click chain and voidling shield beat his skillshot burst."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"cassiopeia","win":["Skill","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia","Malzahar","Cassiopeia","Cassiopeia"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Cassiopeia out-DPSes you here: once she poisons you with Q Noxious Blast or E Twin Fang, her mana-cheap E spam ticks you down while her Q movement speed lets her dodge your E and stay on you, so farm at range and refuse extended trades."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your one clean window: R Nether Grasp is point-click, so at 6 you can suppress immobile Cassiopeia before she turns and lands her R Petrifying Gaze stun, ideally leading with Q silence so she cannot flash-R you first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"She scales harder in lane; her Twin Fang DPS with items out-trades your combo in extended fights and her W Miasma grounds you off the wave, so only commit when your R is up and hers is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Mana-free Twin Fang and grounding outlast your cooldown-bound kit; do not solo her, use R only as a pick under vision or when a teammate has already committed."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge her Q Noxious Blast so she cannot poison you and start the Twin Fang DPS engine","Hit 6 and Q-into-R to point-click suppress her before her R Petrifying Gaze can stun you","Bait her R Petrify or her grounding W, then all-in with suppression while both are on cooldown"],"foe":["Land Q or E to poison you and spam mana-cheap Twin Fang for sustained DPS you cannot answer","Use W Miasma grounding and Q movement speed to zone you off the wave and dodge your E","Land her R Petrifying Gaze first to stun-cancel your suppression attempt"]},"early":"Level 1 is an even skill start decided by the first Q trade, but respect that she wins the moment poison lands, so play the opening carefully and soak CS.","mid":"Levels 2-5 she bullies you with Twin Fang spam and grounding, so weather it and wait for 6, where your point-click R suppresses immobile Cassiopeia before she can land her stun ult.","late":"After her first item her mana-free DPS and grounding outlast your cooldowns; treat R as a pick tool under lockdown rather than a duel button and let your team collapse.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill start; the first Q trade sets the tempo for both of you.","At level 2 her Q movement speed and Twin Fang chip win the short trades.","Level 3 Twin Fang spam on a poisoned you out-DPSes your E waveclear.","Through levels 4-5 her sustain and W grounding zone you off the wave.","At 6 your point-click R suppresses immobile Cassiopeia before she lands her stun ult, your one window.","At her first item scaling Twin Fang DPS out-trades your combo in extended fights.","With two-plus items her mana-free Twin Fang and grounding outlast your cooldown-bound kit."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"diana","win":["Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill","Malzahar","Diana","Diana"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You dominate the early lane: as a ranged mage you poke melee Diana freely, and once E Malefic Visions is up you perma-shove so she either eats poke last-hitting under tower or misses CS, starving her all-in item spike."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 your point-click R Nether Grasp answers her engage: the instant she E Lunar Rushes in, Q to silence and R to suppress her mid-dash while your passive shield and voidlings soak her W shields, flipping her all-in into a kill for you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is where she takes over; her E-R reset combo plus a QSS or Merc treads to break your suppression lets her burst you before your lockdown matters, so ward for her jungler and hold R defensively."},{"when":"Late","text":"Her shielded reset-chain all-in out-damages your single-target lockdown; never face-check her, keep voidlings and shield up, and save R to peel the instant she dives your backline."}],"wants":{"you":["Perma-shove with E and poke melee Diana at range so she cannot farm safely before 6","Bait her E Lunar Rush engage, then Q-R to suppress her mid-dash while your shield eats her W","Roam on your crashed wave to punish her weak early game before her item spike arrives"],"foe":["Reach her first item and buy QSS or Mercs so she can break your R and combo you down","Land Q Crescent Strike into E-R reset burst to kill you before your suppression lands","Scale her shielded all-in so her reset chain out-damages your single-target lockdown"]},"early":"You win levels 1-3 cleanly: ranged base stats and Q let you poke and shove melee Diana under tower, denying her the CS she needs to hit her all-in spike.","mid":"Level 4-5 evens out as her combo comes online, but at 6 your point-click R suppresses her the moment she E-dashes in, and your passive shield eats her W burst, making her engage a losing gamble.","late":"Once Diana itemizes her E-R reset and QSS she out-bursts your lockdown; shift fully to peel, hold R for the dive, and let your team punish her after she blows her combo.","whys":["At level 1 your ranged base stats and Q let you poke melee Diana freely.","At level 2 you shove and deny her Q-shield trades, keeping her off the wave.","Level 3 E waveclear zones her off farm before her all-in comes online.","At levels 4-5 her combo comes online and the lane is even and skill-decided.","At 6 your point-click R suppresses her the instant she E-dashes in while your shield eats her W.","At her first item her E-R reset plus QSS breaks your suppression and kills you.","With two-plus items her shielded all-in and reset chain out-damage your single-target lockdown."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"ekko","win":["Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill","Malzahar","Ekko","Ekko"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You control the early lane: you outrange Ekko and can poke his weak pre-6 trades, and once E Malefic Visions is up you perma-shove so he is stuck last-hitting under tower instead of setting up his W Parallel Convergence stun."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"At 6 your point-click R Nether Grasp beats his engage: Q to silence, then suppress him through his E Phase Dive before he can land his W stun zone, while voidlings and your passive shield absorb his Q-E burst."},{"when":"1st item","text":"He takes over here; his Q-E-R combo bursts you and R Chronobreak rewinds him out of your lockdown or resets the fight, so ward for his roams and hold R until his E and W are down."},{"when":"Late","text":"Ekko's mobility and Chronobreak heal outlast a single-target suppression; never duel him, keep your shield and voidlings up, and save R to peel him off your carries after he commits."}],"wants":{"you":["Perma-shove with E and outrange Ekko so he cannot farm or set up his W stun before 6","Bait his E Phase Dive, then Q-R to suppress him mid-dash while your shield eats his Q-E burst","Roam on the crashed wave to punish his weak early game and deny his snowball"],"foe":["Reach his first item so his Q-E-R combo can burst you before your lockdown lands","Set up W Parallel Convergence for the stun, then all-in with E-R to kill and Chronobreak away","Use R Chronobreak to rewind out of your suppression and reset the trade"]},"early":"You win levels 1-3 clearly: you outrange Ekko and poke his weak early trades, then E waveclear pushes him under tower and denies the CS he needs to spike.","mid":"Level 4-5 is even as his W stun setup comes online, but at 6 your point-click R suppresses him through his E dash before he can W-stun you, punishing any over-commit.","late":"Once Ekko itemizes, his Q-E-R burst and Chronobreak reset out-class your lockdown; shift to peel, hold R for his dive, and let your team collapse after he blows his combo.","whys":["At level 1 you outrange Ekko and poke his weak early trades.","At level 2 you shove and deny his Q harass, holding priority.","Level 3 E waveclear pushes him under tower and starves his farm.","At levels 4-5 his W stun setup comes online and the lane is even and skill-based.","At 6 your point-click R suppresses him through his E dash before he can W-stun you.","At his first item his Q-E-R burst plus Chronobreak reset kills you and escapes your lockdown.","With two-plus items his mobility and rewind heal outlast your single-target suppression."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"fizz","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"The early lane is a neutral standoff: Fizz is melee and cannot punish you without committing, but his E Playful/Trickster untargetability lets him dodge your R later, so just farm with E, hold priority, and do not waste key cooldowns while he holds his hop."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You gain the edge at 6: your voidlings and passive Void Shield soak his R Chum the Waters shark burst, and if he uses E to engage or dodge, R Nether Grasp punishes the window the instant his untargetability ends."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Defensive items like Rylai's or a Seeker's plus voidling peel let you survive his all-in and answer with suppression; itemize to eat his burst rather than trying to out-trade his Q reset."},{"when":"Late","text":"It comes back to even: the whole fight hinges on whether Fizz times E to dodge your R, so bait the hop with a voidling or teammate first, then land the suppression when it is down."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely with E and hold R until Fizz commits E or R, since his untargetable hop can dodge your suppression","Use voidlings and your passive shield to soak his R shark burst, then punish with R when his E is down","Build defensive items so you survive his all-in and answer every dive with lockdown"],"foe":["Hold E Playful/Trickster to dodge your R Nether Grasp cast, then all-in when it is on cooldown","Land R Chum the Waters shark for the burst engage while your suppression is down","Snowball an early kill so his Q reset mobility lets him flank and dodge your combo"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are an even, patient standoff: neither of you can punish cleanly, so soak CS, respect his E untargetability, and never throw R while he can simply hop out of it.","mid":"At 6 you tilt slightly ahead; your voidlings and passive shield absorb his shark all-in, and with defensive items you survive his burst and suppress him the moment his E is spent.","late":"Two-plus items is a coin-flip decided by his E timing versus your R cast, so make him blow the hop first with a voidling or ally, then land the suppression to win the exchange.","whys":["Level 1 is even; melee Fizz cannot punish you and you cannot punish his pool.","At level 2 trades stay neutral with both of you focused on farming.","Level 3 pits your E waveclear against his W sustain, roughly even.","At levels 4-5 neither commits pre-item; he holds E to dodge and you hold R.","At 6 your voidlings and passive shield soak his shark burst and R punishes a used E.","At your first item defensive buys plus voidling peel let you survive his all-in and answer with suppression.","With two-plus items it is even, decided by whether he times E to dodge your R."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"galio","win":["Skill","Skill","Galio","Galio","Galio","Galio","Galio"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Galio takes over from level 3: his W Shield of Durand halves your magic damage on the block, and since your entire kit is magic, your poke and E chip do far less while his Q Winds of War tornado out-ranges you, so just farm and give up the aggressive trades."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"His global R Hero's Entrance makes him a roaming nightmare while his tankiness shrugs your magic burst; do not expect to solo-kill him, and track his R so you can ping and follow when he flashes across the map to a fight."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With any MR and his W damage reduction, your R Nether Grasp barely dents him; you can still suppress him to lock him for your team, but you will not burn him down one-on-one."},{"when":"Late","text":"He builds tanky, ults across the map and taunts your carries; your single-target magic lockdown does too little to him, so use R to peel him off your backline rather than to kill."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm safely levels 1-2 while the lane is even, before his W damage reduction comes online","Use R to lock Galio for your team rather than trying to solo-kill through his magic resistance","Track his global R and match his roams so he cannot get a free pick on your side lanes"],"foe":["Turn on W Shield of Durand to halve your magic damage and neutralize your poke and combo","Roam with global R Hero's Entrance to punish your side lanes while shrugging your burst","Build MR and tankiness so your single-target magic lockdown does too little to matter"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even skill start; you can shove while he farms behind his W shield, so bank CS before his damage reduction turns the lane against you.","mid":"From 3 to 6 Galio wins outright: his W halves your magic damage, his Q out-pokes you, and his global R lets him roam-punish while tanking anything you throw at him.","late":"He itemizes tanky, ults across the map and taunts your carries; your magic lockdown does too little, so spend R peeling him off your backline instead of dueling.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill start; neither threatens before abilities come online.","At level 2 you shove while he farms behind W, keeping it neutral.","At level 3 his W halves your magic damage and his Q tornado out-pokes you.","Through levels 4-5 his W reduction and shield make your poke and combo ineffective.","At 6 his global R and tankiness let him roam-punish while shrugging your magic burst.","At his first item MR plus W reduction blunt your whole kit and your R barely dents him.","With two-plus items he builds tanky, ults across the map, and your single-target magic lockdown does too little."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"hwei","win":["Hwei","Hwei","Hwei","Hwei","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Hwei's window: his QQ (Devastating Fire) and QE (Severing Bolt) out-range everything you have, so he chunks you while you last-hit under his paint zone. Sidestep the slow lines and only step up to refresh Malefic Visions on the caster minions."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your window flips hard. Nether Grasp is point-and-click and Hwei has no dash to escape it, so once E is ticking you can R him mid-poke, add Q silence and voidlings, and delete him before he can EE (Crushing Maelstrom) knockup or ER (Stirring Lands) pull free."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Blackfire Torch/Liandry's plus your DoT means a landed R is a kill on a squishy Hwei every cooldown. Look for it the instant your passive Void Shift is up so his poke can't punish the walk-in."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even fight: if he lands his W (Fleeting Currents) speed and R zone he can kite your all-in, but you only need one clean R to remove him from the teamfight. Flank angles that hide your approach win it."}],"wants":{"you":["Hit level 6 with your passive Void Shift up before you commit","A landed R while E and voidlings are already ticking on him","Fog-of-war or flank angles so his poke can't punish your walk-in"],"foe":["Long-range QQ/QE poke that chips you below all-in health","Keeping the full screen of distance so you can never reach R range","His R zone and W speed to kite once you dash in"]},"early":"You lose the first five levels of poke and there is no fixing that with mechanics. Hwei's Q subjects out-range your auto and your Malefic Visions harass, so respect the QE zap and the slow QQ lines and do not walk into his paint. Farm with E and voidling shove, keep your health above his combo threshold, and accept that you will be down some HP heading into six. Do not flash-poke back; you win by surviving to your spike, not by trading kits you cannot win.","mid":"Six is where the matchup inverts. Land Malefic Visions, wait for Void Shift, then R the immobile Hwei and chain Q silence plus voidlings for the kill. He has no reliable escape from point-and-click suppression, so every time your ult is up he has to play scared and give up wave and poke priority. Use that respect to shove and roam or set up your jungler on his side.","late":"Both fully itemized it comes down to spacing: if you reach him he dies to R plus DoT, if his poke and R zone keep you out he wins the exchange. Build a bit of survivability so his combo can't delete you on the approach, and pick your R angles from fog. One suppression on Hwei ends the fight for his team.","whys":["Hwei's QQ and QE lines out-range your auto and Malefic Visions harass, so he pokes you freely at level 1.","His QE (Severing Bolt) and paint zone punish you as you last-hit under his superior range.","With all three subjects online his combo poke chunks you before your voidlings and E can trade back.","He stacks poke and zones you off the wave with W paint and the E disruption pool, holding the range gap.","Your R suppresses the immobile Hwei and, chained with E and voidlings, kills him before he can EE or ER out.","Your first-item burst plus DoT lets a landed R delete a squishy Hwei on cooldown.","Fully itemized it comes down to whether you reach R range before his poke and R zone win the spacing."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"irelia","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Irelia","Irelia","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Even, but tense. Irelia wants a Q (Bladesurge) reset off a minion into you with W (Defiant Dance) up for the damage reduction and true-damage return. Do not auto her while W is active. Your answer is Q silence on her dash-in and Void Shift eating the burst; shove with E and voidlings so she cannot freely stack passive."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Irelia's window. Her level-6 R (Vanguard's Edge) engage plus a landed E (Flawless Duet) stun can interrupt your Nether Grasp channel entirely and burst you before you lock her. Hold R for after her E is used, or peel it with Q silence and passive first."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still her spike. Trinity Force/Bork lets her all-in through your Void Shift, and any E stun mid-fight cancels your R. Don't commit ult until her E dagger is spent or you have Zhonya's to answer her follow-up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Back to even. With Zhonya's and a full DoT setup you survive her Q gap-close and R her mid-combo. Space so her E can't stun you before your channel finishes and she loses the duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait her E (Flawless Duet) stun before you commit Nether Grasp","Shove with E so she can't stack Q passive for the all-in","Zhonya's plus DoT to survive her dash and R her mid-combo"],"foe":["A Q reset off a minion into an E stun to cancel your R","W (Defiant Dance) up so your autos and voidlings feed her return","Her level-6 R engage and Trinity/Bork spike to burst through your passive"]},"early":"The first four levels are genuinely even and you should farm them cleanly. Irelia can look for a Q-reset all-in but you have real answers: Q silence stops her mid-dash, Void Shift shields her burst, and your voidlings punish her if she commits without a stun. Never trade into an active W (Defiant Dance) or you feed the true-damage return. Shove with Malefic Visions to deny her passive stacks on the wave and keep priority so her jungler can't set up a dive.","mid":"This is her hill. At six her R plus E stun can interrupt Nether Grasp, and her Trinity/Bork timing lets her all-in through your shield, so the six-to-first-item stretch is where she kills you. Discipline your R: never open with it into an available E, because a stun cancels the channel and wastes your only lockdown. Bait the E with a step-back or Q, then suppress. If she has a numbers or item lead, play safe under tower and wait for the fight to even back out.","late":"Once you have Zhonya's and core DoT the matchup returns to even. You can eat her engage, stasis her R, and point-and-click suppress her out of the fight. Space around her E so she can't cancel your ult, and remember your R on a dive-happy Irelia protects your whole backline. One clean suppression turns her all-in into her death.","whys":["Neither commits at level 1; you shove with Malefic Visions while she stacks Q passive on minions, an even start.","She looks for a W-guarded trade, you look to E-shove and poke back, roughly even.","Her Q-E all-in is real but your Q silence and Void Shift answer it, keeping the trade even.","You push and set up roams while she farms stacks; neither lands a clean kill, still even.","Her level-6 R engage plus E stun can interrupt your Nether Grasp channel and burst you before you lock her.","Her Trinity/Bork spike lets her all-in through your passive, and an E stun cancels your R before it finishes.","With Zhonya's and a full DoT setup you survive her dash and R her mid-combo, evening the fight."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"karma","win":["Skill","Skill","Karma","Karma","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Karma's window. With Mantra online her empowered RQ (Inner Flame) is a huge cone of poke that out-ranges your voidling trades, and her W (Focused Resolve) tether roots you if you walk up carelessly. Dodge the Q line, don't stand in the RQ detonation radius, and farm with E rather than contesting poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You flip it. Nether Grasp suppresses Karma straight through her E (Inspire) speed boost, and with Malefic Visions plus Q silence plus voidlings she dies before Mantra-W or a shield can save her. Wait for Void Shift, then walk her down."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your DoT plus first-item burst means a landed R is a kill on a squishy enchanter every cooldown. She has no hard escape, so any time your ult is up she has to give you wave and roam priority."},{"when":"Late","text":"You out-scale her utility kit. A point-and-click R is a guaranteed pick that her shields can only partially absorb, and in teamfights suppressing Karma removes her whole peel. Look for flank R angles."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 6 and R her through the E speed boost","Void Shift up so her RQ poke can't punish the walk-in","Land R while E and voidlings are already ticking for the kill"],"foe":["Mantra-empowered RQ poke to chunk you before six","Her W tether and E speed to zone you off the wave","Keeping range so you never close to Nether Grasp distance"]},"early":"The first two levels are a wash and then Karma's Mantra poke takes over. Her RQ is a wide, long cone that out-ranges your kit, so levels three to five you are on the back foot, dodging Q lines and farming with Malefic Visions instead of trading. Never walk into W (Focused Resolve) range at low health or the tether plus poke can chunk you out. Stay patient, keep your HP up, and don't waste your ult before six trying to answer her.","mid":"Six is your inflection point. Karma is squishy and her only mobility is the E speed boost, which does nothing against point-and-click suppression, so once Malefic Visions is ticking you R her and chain silence plus voidlings for the kill. Every cooldown of your ult forces her to respect you, and you convert that into wave control, roams, and jungle setups. Play for the Void Shift-up walk-in rather than fishing through her poke.","late":"You scale past her cleanly. Your DoT and burst let a landed R delete her, and in fights suppressing Karma strips your enemy team of a huge chunk of peel and shielding. Take flank angles so her range advantage never matters, and treat every R on her as a guaranteed pick her Mantra can't fully save.","whys":["Karma's Q poke versus your Malefic Visions shove is a wash at first-blood level.","She pokes with Q, you shove and look to trade back, roughly even.","Her Mantra-empowered RQ poke chunks you and out-ranges your voidling trades.","Repeated RQ poke and her W tether zone you off the wave and keep her health lead.","Your R suppresses Karma through her E speed and, with E plus voidlings, kills her before Mantra shields save her.","Your DoT plus first-item burst lets R delete a squishy Karma on each cooldown.","You out-scale her utility kit; a landed R is a guaranteed pick her shields can't fully absorb."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"kassadin","win":["Malzahar","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your window from the start. Kassadin is melee and cannot contest Malefic Visions, so perma-shove with E and voidlings, chunk him whenever he steps up to CS, and deny him farm. His Q (Null Sphere) shield-silence blocks a little poke, so bait it before you commit, but you dictate the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still yours. Kassadin's level-6 Riftwalk is his identity but it does not save him from point-and-click R; Nether Grasp suppresses him through the blink attempt and Void Shift shrugs off his weak pre-scaling all-in. Kill him or keep him pinned under tower."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your last clean window before he comes online. Your DoT plus R burst kills him and, more importantly, keeps him off his item and R-stack timings. Every time you deny his back you delay the point where he takes over."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even to losing. Once Kassadin has his core AP and Riftwalk stacks, his blink mobility dodges your R and he out-scales you. Ward for his roams, group with your team, and use R to peel his dive rather than duel him."}],"wants":{"you":["Perma-shove with E to starve the melee Kassadin of CS","Deny his first item and R-stack timings with repeated pressure","Land R before he scales, while Void Shift eats his weak all-in"],"foe":["Survive laning phase to his AP core and Riftwalk stacks","Use Q shield-silence to block your poke and farm safely","Reach the late game where R mobility dodges your Nether Grasp"]},"early":"This is a lane you should win outright because Kassadin is helpless early. He is melee, so every time he walks up for a last hit you hit him with Malefic Visions and voidlings, and there is nothing he can do about it. Perma-shove, deny CS, and set up your jungler for dives. His only tool is Q (Null Sphere) to shield and silence a bit of your poke, so bait it before you commit your combo. Keep the pressure relentless.","mid":"Six through first item stays firmly in your favour. His Riftwalk is a blink but Nether Grasp is point-and-click, so it locks him through the escape attempt, and your passive eats his feeble pre-scaling damage. Your job here is not just to kill him but to keep him starved: every denied back and every lost wave delays the timer where Kassadin becomes a monster. Shove, roam, and snowball your side of the map before he can catch up.","late":"Once he stacks AP and Riftwalk the matchup slips to even or worse. His mobility lets him dodge your R and flank your carries, so stop trying to solo him. Group with your team, ward his roam paths, and save Nether Grasp to lock him when he dives your backline rather than dueling. Your early lead is your insurance; close the game before his scaling fully arrives.","whys":["Kassadin is melee and can't contest your Malefic Visions harass, so you chunk him freely at level 1.","His Q shield-silence blocks some of your poke, evening the early trade slightly.","He uses Q to block your Q silence and farm safely; the lane settles even before your spike.","You perma-shove with E and voidlings, denying the melee Kassadin CS and setting up roams while he's stuck.","Your R suppresses him through his Riftwalk attempts and your passive shrugs off his weak all-in.","Before his scaling is online, your DoT plus R burst kills him and keeps him off his item timings.","Once Kassadin has his AP core and R stacks, his blink mobility dodges your R and he out-scales, evening things."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"katarina","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Even and skill-based. Katarina farms with Q (Bouncing Blade) daggers and looks for an E (Shunpo) reset all-in onto a dagger. Deny her free daggers by shoving, keep Q silence ready to interrupt her combo, and don't stand next to a live dagger at low health. Void Shift eats her opening burst if she commits."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your window opens wide. Nether Grasp suppresses Katarina and hard-cancels her R (Death Lotus) channel, and your passive absorbs the burst that would set up her resets. Once E is ticking, R her out of any all-in she starts."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still yours. Your DoT plus point-and-click R shuts her down every time she engages, and because she needs a kill or dagger reset to snowball, denying that starves her. Keep R for the moment she Shunpos in."},{"when":"Late","text":"Back to skill. A fed Katarina can flank from fog and one-shot a squishy before you can turn R on her, or she can bait Void Shift and wait it out. Track her, keep vision, and save your ult to peel her dive rather than duel."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 6 and R her to cancel Death Lotus and lock the reset chain","Void Shift up to eat her opening Shunpo burst","Shove to deny free Q daggers she resets on"],"foe":["Free Q daggers to Shunpo-reset an all-in","Bait or wait out your Void Shift before committing","A fog flank to one-shot a squishy before you can R her"]},"early":"The opening levels are even and decided by execution. Katarina wants to farm daggers with Q and then E-reset into an all-in, so your job is to deny her setup: shove with Malefic Visions, keep Q (Call of the Void) ready to silence her mid-combo, and never linger beside a live dagger when low. If she commits without a clean reset, Void Shift shields the burst and your voidlings punish her. Don't overextend into jungle pressure since she thrives on early skirmishes.","mid":"Six is where you take control. Your R suppresses her and cancels Death Lotus outright, so any all-in she starts ends with her dead and no reset to bail her out. Your passive eating her initial burst means she often can't even open the fight cleanly. Hold Nether Grasp for the moment she Shunpos in rather than throwing it early, and use the respect it generates to shove and roam. She is not allowed to snowball if she can't finish a kill.","late":"Fully itemized it swings back to skill. A fed Katarina flanks from fog and can delete a squishy before you get R off, or she baits your passive and waits the cooldown. Keep vision on her flanks, group with your team, and treat your ult as a peel tool for whichever carry she dives. If you catch her mid-R the fight is over; if she catches you first it's a coinflip.","whys":["She farms with Q daggers, you shove with Malefic Visions; neither commits, even.","Her Q-E poke versus your shove-and-poke stays even before ultimates.","Her all-in with an E reset threatens, but your Q silence and Void Shift hold it even.","You push and she looks to roam or reset; the lane stays even as both farm.","Your R suppresses Katarina and cancels her Death Lotus channel, and your passive eats her burst.","Your DoT plus point-and-click R shuts her down every time she engages, denying resets.","A fed Katarina can flank and one-shot a squishy before you R her, or wait out your passive, evening it."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"leblanc","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","LeBlanc","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Even and skill-based. LeBlanc pokes with Q (Sigil of Malice) and W (Distortion) but risks a lot committing into your kit. Punish a used W with Q silence and voidlings, keep Void Shift as an anti-burst buffer, and shove with E so she can't freely poke and reposition. Sidestep her E (Ethereal Chains) or the root sets up her combo."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your window. Nether Grasp suppresses her and cancels the Distortion escape, and Void Shift eats her QWE burst so she can't kill you through it. Wait for your passive, then R her the moment she dashes in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Her spike. A Ludens/Malignance timing lets her W-in, land E (Ethereal Chains) root, and burst you down before your R can land, then W back out. Don't sit at combo-threshold HP, keep passive up, and hug the range where she can't chain-root you."},{"when":"Late","text":"Back to you. With Zhonya's and full DoT your passive and R lock her down and she can't kill through the shield. Bait the combo, stasis it, then suppress her out of the fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 6 with Void Shift up to eat the QWE burst","R her the instant she W-dashes in to cancel Distortion","Zhonya's plus DoT so she can't kill through your shield"],"foe":["A Ludens/Malignance spike to one-shot before your R lands","E (Ethereal Chains) root to lock the combo then W out","Catch you at combo-threshold HP with your passive down"]},"early":"The first four levels are even and about discipline. LeBlanc can Q-W poke but every commitment risks her getting Q-silenced and eaten by your voidlings, so make her pay for greedy steps. Shove with Malefic Visions to deny her the tempo she wants for poke-and-reposition, and always sidestep E (Ethereal Chains) because the root is what turns her poke into a kill. Keep Void Shift as your anti-burst insurance and don't fall below the health where her full combo one-shots.","mid":"Six is your best window: point-and-click R suppresses her, cancels the Distortion escape, and your passive absorbs the opening burst, so a committed LeBlanc simply dies. But respect her first-item spike immediately after, because a Ludens or Malignance timing lets her W-in, E-root, and delete you before you can channel, then W safely away. Manage that by keeping your passive up, never sitting at combo HP, and holding R for her dash-in rather than fishing. Between her item timings you own the lane.","late":"With Zhonya's and core DoT the matchup is firmly yours again. Her burst can't kill through your shield and stasis, and one clean Nether Grasp removes her from the fight entirely. Bait her combo, stasis the damage, then R her as she's committed. She only wins the late fight if she catches you alone with everything up, so group and keep your passive as a buffer.","whys":["She can Q poke but you shove with Malefic Visions and nothing dies, even.","Her W-Q poke versus your shove stays even before she has her full combo.","Her QWE burst threatens but your Void Shift and Q silence keep it even.","You shove and she looks to roam with W mobility; neither gets a clean kill, even.","Your R suppresses her and cancels her Distortion escape, and your passive eats the combo before she bursts.","Her Ludens/Malignance spike lets her W-in, E-root and burst you before R lands, then W out.","With Zhonya's and full DoT your passive and R lock her down; she can't kill through the shield and you delete her."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"lissandra","win":["Lissandra","Lissandra","Lissandra","Lissandra","Lissandra","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Lissandra's window and it lasts a while. Her Q (Ice Shard) out-ranges your poke and her W (Ring of Frost) root sets up an all-in your voidlings can't answer, while E (Glide) gives her the mobility to dive your shove and get back out. Farm safe with Malefic Visions, dodge Q, and never let her walk into W range on you at low HP."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Still hers. Her R (Frozen Tomb) can lock you for the all-in or self-cast to stasis out of your Nether Grasp, breaking the suppression. Her W-Q combo still out-damages your kit, so play under tower and don't duel her yet."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You flip it here. Your DoT and R burst come fully online, and her control kit can't save her from the chunk once E is ticking and you suppress her. Look for the R the moment your passive is up."},{"when":"Late","text":"Yours. You out-scale her control kit, a landed R is a guaranteed pick, and your DoT grinds her down in extended fights. In teamfights suppressing Lissandra strips her whole engage; take flank angles she can't peel."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the level 1-5 poke to your first-item DoT spike","R her with Void Shift up before her R can peel or stasis it","Flank angles late where a guaranteed R removes her engage"],"foe":["Q poke and W root all-in to chunk you before six","E mobility to dive your shove and escape","Self-cast R stasis to break your Nether Grasp suppression"]},"early":"You are behind for the entire early game and you have to accept it. Lissandra's Q out-ranges you, her W (Ring of Frost) root turns any misstep into a kill, and E (Glide) lets her engage your shove and glide back to safety. There is no trade you win here, so farm with Malefic Visions from max range, dodge her Q, and keep your health above her W-Q all-in threshold. Don't waste your ult trying to answer her before your items; just survive to your spike.","mid":"Six does not save you the way it does in most matchups, because her R (Frozen Tomb) can either lock you for the all-in or self-cast to stasis and break your suppression mid-channel. She still out-damages you with W-Q, so stay disciplined, farm under tower, and pick your moments. The turn comes at first item: once your DoT and burst are online, a landed Nether Grasp with Void Shift up chunks her past what her control kit can undo. Play patient and let the game come to your scaling.","late":"This is where you win. You out-scale her utility kit outright, your DoT grinds her down in any extended fight, and a point-and-click R on Lissandra is a guaranteed pick that removes her team's primary engage before she can flash-R the backline. Take angles from fog she can't peel, and if she blows R to stasis, your voidlings and DoT keep ticking while your team collapses. Close from a position of scaling strength, not early trades.","whys":["Her Q poke out-ranges you and she can all-in with W root, taking the level-1 edge.","Her W root plus Q chunk threatens a kill your voidlings can't answer yet.","With E mobility and the W-Q combo she out-trades and can dive your shove, staying ahead.","Her sustained Q poke and root all-in keep you on the back foot as she controls the wave.","Her R can lock you or self-stasis to peel your Nether Grasp, and her all-in still out-damages your combo.","Your DoT and R burst come online; you suppress her and her utility can't save her from the chunk.","You out-scale her control kit; a landed R is a guaranteed pick and your DoT grinds her down late."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"locke","win":["Locke","Locke","Skill","Skill","Locke","Skill","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Locke has the early aggression here, so play the wave, not the trade. You have no dash and your kill threat is Nether Grasp at 6, meaning any all-in Locke wins before that is pure profit for him. Shove with Void Swarm and Malefic Visions, hold Void Shift for his opener, and last-hit from max range so he can't open on you cleanly."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Locke keeps a slight edge at his own 6 spike, but your R changes the math the moment you also hit it. Point-click Nether Grasp suppresses him with no counterplay once landed, so bait his commit, then ult, the suppression plus your DoTs is your kill pattern. Don't ult into an unspent defensive if he holds one."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Evens out as your DPS comes online. Your sustained damage and point-click R stabilize the lane, and Void Shift denies his engage by eating the first spell of his combo, so trades stop being one-sided."},{"when":"Late","text":"A coin-flip that your ult tilts in reachable fights. Save R for whoever dives your carry, or use it on Locke directly; suppression is your equalizer whenever he commits onto you."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive to 6 without giving an early all-in","Hold Void Shift to absorb his opener","Farm at max range and let your waveclear out-tempo him"],"foe":["Use his early-game edge to all-in before your ult","Catch you with Void Shift down","Snowball a lead before your item DPS stabilizes the lane"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Locke's early aggression; with no dash and no pre-6 kill threat you soak safely, buffer his opener with Void Shift, and refuse the trade.","mid":"Levels 3-5 settle toward even as your waveclear holds serve, though Locke reclaims an edge at his 6 spike until your Nether Grasp gives you an undodgeable answer of your own.","late":"From first item on it evens and skill decides it, your point-click R and ramping DPS stabilize things while Void Shift blocks his engage, making any reachable fight a suppression you can win.","whys":["Level 1 favours Locke, whose early aggression pressures a slow, dash-less Malzahar.","Level 2 favours Locke, who can all-in before your pre-6 kit offers any answer.","Level 3 is even as your waveclear and Void Shift let you refuse his trades.","Levels 4-5 stay even, decided by wave control rather than raw stats.","Level 6 favours Locke's spike, holding a slight edge until your own ult fully answers it.","First item is even as your point-click R and DPS stabilize the lane.","With two-plus items it stays skill-based, your suppression equalizing any fight he commits to."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"lux","win":["Skill","Skill","Lux","Lux","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Lux's window, not yours. With Light Binding (Q), Lucent Singularity (E) and Prismatic Barrier she out-ranges everything you have; her Q root into E poke chunks you while you shove waves. Hold Void Shift to eat a Q, hug the wave, and last-hit under tower rather than stepping up to trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Nether Grasp (R) flips the lane. Lux has zero mobility and no way to break your channel once you Flash-suppress her, and your R applies Malefic Visions for follow-up. If she Qs and whiffs, that's your all-in; walk her down while your Voidlings and E finish."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Post-Blackfire Torch/Liandry's your sustained damage and point-click R outkill her burst-and-run pattern. Void Shift also neutralizes her only engage tool by blocking the Q that sets up her combo, so she can't reliably start a fight on you."},{"when":"Late","text":"You scale past her in any skirmish where she can be reached. Save R for whoever dives your carry, or use it to delete Lux herself since her one Q is her whole self-peel."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 6 even in CS and un-poked","Bait or block her Light Binding (Q) with Void Shift before you commit","Sidestep so her Lucent Singularity (E) can't zone you off the wave"],"foe":["Land Q root into E to chunk you repeatedly before 6","Keep the wave in the middle and poke you every time you step to CS","Kill you or force back before your R comes online"]},"early":"Lane starts even at 1-2 while you both ranged-trade auto for auto and set up your E, Malefic Visions, on the wave; nobody has a kill threat yet.","mid":"Levels 3-5 belong to Lux: her Q root, E poke and shield out-range you and punish every step toward the wave, so play safe, use Void Shift as a poke buffer, and farm to 6.","late":"From 6 on you take over; Nether Grasp suppresses an immobile Lux with no escape, and your item-backed DPS plus Void Shift blocking her engage flips the matchup firmly your way.","whys":["Level 1 is even, both trading ranged autos and dropping Malefic Visions with no kill pressure yet.","Level 2 stays even, as neither of you has enough to convert a trade into a kill.","Level 3 favours Lux, whose Q-into-E poke combo out-ranges you and zones you off the wave.","Levels 4-5 favour Lux, whose superior poke and shield let her win every extended trade before your ult.","Level 6 favours Malzahar, whose Nether Grasp suppresses an immobile Lux with no way to break the channel.","First item favours Malzahar, whose sustained DPS and point-click R outkill her burst while Void Shift blocks her Q engage.","With two-plus items Malzahar stays ahead, outscaling and deleting a Lux who only has one Q to peel herself."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"mel","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Even, skill-based farm lane. Mel's Radiant Volley (Q) pokes as she stacks Overwhelm marks, but you match her waveclear with Void Swarm and Malefic Visions. The real trap is her Rebuttal (W): it can reflect a projectile and CC back at you, so never fire a committal spell into an up W."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your window. Nether Grasp (R) point-blank suppresses her and can't be dodged, but respect her W timer, if she Rebuttals your channel you feed it. Bait the W with an auto or E, then ult when it's down and she has no escape from the suppression."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You edge ahead once your DPS comes online; a suppressed Mel dies inside your R plus Malefic Visions and Voidling stacks. Keep tracking her W cooldown, that single button is the only thing that saves her from a clean pick."},{"when":"Late","text":"Evens back out. Mel's Solar Snare (R) and execute-scaling Overwhelm give her real teamfight value, and her Rebuttal can turn your single-target ult against you, so ult a diver instead of forcing it into her reflect."}],"wants":{"you":["Bait out Rebuttal (W) before you commit R or a big spell","Hit 6 healthy and pick a moment her W is down","Use Void Shift to absorb her Radiant Volley poke while farming"],"foe":["Reflect your engage spell or ult back with Rebuttal (W)","Stack Overwhelm marks and poke you down across the mid game","Reach late where Solar Snare and execute damage scale in fights"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even farm lane; you both ranged-poke and set up waveclear, and neither Radiant Volley nor your Q converts to a kill yet.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay skill-matched, she pokes with Q and Overwhelm while you clear with W and E, the whole dance revolving around whether her Rebuttal is up.","late":"At 6 you spike with Nether Grasp on an immobile target, but past two items it re-evens as her ult, execute scaling and reflect give her the tools to fight back and punish a forced R.","whys":["Level 1 is even, a farm-and-poke standoff where neither of you threatens a kill.","Level 2 stays even as both of you just clear and trade autos.","Level 3 is skill-based, her Q poke against your waveclear with the Rebuttal timer deciding trades.","Levels 4-5 remain even, decided by whether you respect her W rather than by raw stats.","Level 6 favours Malzahar, whose undodgeable Nether Grasp suppresses an immobile Mel when her W is down.","First item favours Malzahar, whose online DPS turns a suppressed Mel into a clean kill.","With two-plus items it evens out, as Mel's ult, execute scaling and reflect let her fight back and punish a forced R."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"naafiri","win":["Skill","Naafiri","Naafiri","Naafiri","Malzahar","Naafiri","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Naafiri's window and the scary one. Once her Packmates are up she uses Darkin Daggers (Q) and the Hounds' Pursuit setup with Evolved Packmate (W) dash to close and burst you, and you have no dash to escape. Shove and freeze awkwardly, hug tower, and hold Void Shift for her W engage so the first hit doesn't chunk you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You flip it. Nether Grasp (R) point-click suppresses her mid-dash and shuts the entire all-in down, no dagger reset, no execute. If she W's onto you, ult her on the spot; the suppression plus Malefic Visions and Voidlings turns her dive into her death."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Back to her favour if you let her roam. Her ultimate gives movement speed and lets her collapse on side lanes, so she snowballs off picks elsewhere even when she can't kill you 1v1. Ward wide and match her roam timers or she gets fed off your team."},{"when":"Late","text":"You reclaim it. Point-click R hard-counters a single-target diver like Naafiri, so you sit on your carry and delete her the instant she commits her R dash in. She has no way to fight through the suppression."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 6 without being burst under her Packmate dive","Save Void Shift for her Evolved Packmate (W) engage","Answer her roams instead of dueling her pre-6"],"foe":["Get Packmates online and all-in with W dash plus Q daggers","Use her R movement speed to roam and snowball side lanes","Kill you before 6 while you have no escape"]},"early":"Level 1 is even before her pack is built, but she is already looking to set up the trades that come online a level later.","mid":"Levels 2-5 are Naafiri's: Packmate daggers and her W dash let her close and burst a mobility-less Malzahar, so you farm safe, freeze if you can, and buffer her engage with Void Shift.","late":"From 6 you swing it with Nether Grasp suppressing her dive, though her R roams can tilt the map at first item, past two items your point-click ult cleanly counters her single-target all-in.","whys":["Level 1 is even, played before her Packmates come online and enable her burst.","Level 2 favours Naafiri as her pack lets her start dagger-and-dash trades you can't escape.","Level 3 favours Naafiri, whose W dash and Q daggers out-burst a mobility-less Malzahar.","Levels 4-5 favour Naafiri, whose all-in threat keeps you pinned under tower.","Level 6 favours Malzahar, whose point-click Nether Grasp suppresses her mid-dive and cancels the all-in.","First item favours Naafiri, whose ult movement speed lets her roam and snowball other lanes.","With two-plus items Malzahar retakes it, as point-click R hard-counters her single-target dive."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"neeko","win":["Neeko","Neeko","Neeko","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early it's Neeko's lane. Tangle-Barbs (Q) and Blooming Burst (E) out-poke and out-clear you, and Shapesplitter (W) plus her passive disguise let her set up roams you can't follow. Farm safe, respect the root, and track her, if her clone walks mid she's ganking a sidelane."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your spike. Nether Grasp (R) suppresses her before she can channel Pop Blossom, and it can't be dodged once you land it. If she jumps in for her ult, ult her first; the suppression cancels her whole teamfight threat and applies Malefic Visions."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You pull ahead. Your sustained DPS and point-click R punish an immobile Neeko whose only escape is W's brief speed, while Void Shift eats her Q root to deny the engage that sets up her burst."},{"when":"Late","text":"You stay ahead in any reachable fight; save R to interrupt her Pop Blossom or to delete her outright, since without that channel she brings little to a skirmish against you."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 6 even and un-rooted","Track her clone and roams instead of dueling early","Hold Void Shift for her Tangle-Barbs (Q) root"],"foe":["Poke you with Q and E and zone you off the wave","Roam with Shapesplitter (W) and her passive disguise","Land Pop Blossom (R) engage before you can suppress her"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are Neeko's: her Q root, E burst and disguise-roam pressure out-tempo you, so play the wave safe and give up nothing to the poke.","mid":"By levels 4-5 it evens as your waveclear catches up and you approach 6, the point where the lane inverts.","late":"From 6 on you take control, Nether Grasp suppresses her before Pop Blossom and item DPS lets you delete an immobile target, with Void Shift blocking the Q that starts her combo.","whys":["Level 1 favours Neeko, whose Q and E poke out-range and out-clear you from the start.","Level 2 favours Neeko, whose burst and roam threat keep you on the back foot.","Level 3 favours Neeko, whose disguise roams and poke pressure out-tempo a slow Malzahar.","Levels 4-5 are even as your waveclear catches up heading into 6.","Level 6 favours Malzahar, whose Nether Grasp suppresses her before she can land Pop Blossom.","First item favours Malzahar, whose DPS and point-click R punish an immobile Neeko.","With two-plus items Malzahar stays ahead, deleting her in any reachable fight while blocking her Q engage."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"orianna","win":["Orianna","Orianna","Orianna","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Orianna"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Orianna owns this phase. Command: Attack (Q) into Command: Dissonance (E) gives her free poke and self-peel at a range you can't match, and her ball control lets her clear waves and zone you off CS without commitment. Buffer the Q poke with Void Shift, farm on your side, and don't step up into her ball."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your window opens. Nether Grasp (R) suppresses an immobile Ori before she can land Command: Shockwave, and she has no dash to break it. If you can Flash-R or catch her stepping up, the suppression plus Malefic Visions ends her; just respect that her Shockwave can peel a teammate off you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You edge ahead 1v1. Your point-click R and sustained DPS beat her out when the fight is isolated, and Void Shift eating her Q denies the poke that chips you down. Keep the lane small and duel her, don't let it become a group fight yet."},{"when":"Late","text":"Tilts back to Orianna in teamfights. Command: Shockwave is a game-swinging AoE that outvalues your single-target R when both sides group, so your job is to R the diver on your carry, not to trade ults with her in a 5v5."}],"wants":{"you":["Isolate her for a 1v1 where point-click R wins","Reach 6 without being poked below half","Hold Void Shift for her Command: Attack (Q) poke"],"foe":["Poke with Q-E and control the wave from max range","Keep fights grouped so Command: Shockwave (R) outvalues yours","Zone you off CS with her ball before 6"]},"early":"Levels 1-3 are Orianna's: her ball gives free poke and superior waveclear that pushes you in and denies farm, so soak safely and buffer with Void Shift.","mid":"Level 4-5 evens as you close on 6, then Nether Grasp lets you suppress an immobile Ori and win isolated fights through first item.","late":"Past two items it swings back to her, Command: Shockwave is a teamfight ultimate that outvalues your single-target suppression once both teams group, so use R defensively on divers instead.","whys":["Level 1 favours Orianna, whose ball gives free poke and waveclear you can't contest.","Level 2 favours Orianna, whose Q-E poke and range zone you off the wave.","Level 3 favours Orianna, whose superior clear and control keep you pinned under tower.","Levels 4-5 are even as you reach 6 and your kill threat comes online.","Level 6 favours Malzahar, whose Nether Grasp suppresses an immobile Ori with no dash to escape.","First item favours Malzahar, whose point-click R and DPS win the isolated 1v1.","With two-plus items Orianna retakes it, as Command: Shockwave outvalues your single-target ult in grouped fights."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"pantheon","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Skill lane that you can play cleanly. Pantheon wants to Comet Spear (Q) poke and W-stun all-in, but your passive Void Shift blocks his first spear or stun, and your waveclear with Void Swarm and Malefic Visions keeps you at range. Don't walk into W range with your shield down and he can't open on you."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Hard flip in your favour. Nether Grasp (R) point-click suppresses him the instant he Ws in, cancelling the whole combo, no Aegis, no reset. If he all-ins, ult him mid-jump; the suppression plus Malefic Visions and Voidlings turns his dive into a free kill for you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You pull clearly ahead. Pantheon's damage falls off as yours ramps, and your point-click R plus Void Shift blocking his engage means he simply can't open a fight on you profitably anymore."},{"when":"Late","text":"You dominate a reachable Pantheon. His teamfight is a single Grand Starfall dive, and your R hard-counters exactly that, so sit on your carry and suppress him the moment he lands."}],"wants":{"you":["Keep Void Shift up to block his Comet Spear (Q) or Aegis stun (W)","Reach 6 and hold R for his all-in","Farm at range with W and E out of W-stun distance"],"foe":["Land W stun into Q to burst you before 6","Poke you down with Comet Spear while your shield is down","All-in or roam before your ult and item DPS come online"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are skill-based; Pantheon pokes with Q but Void Shift blocks his opener, so you farm safely and deny him a clean all-in.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay even as he looks for a W-stun engage and you answer with waveclear and a shield timer he has to respect.","late":"From 6 you take over hard, Nether Grasp point-click suppresses his all-in and dive, and your scaling DPS plus Void Shift blocking his engage leaves a falloff-prone Pantheon with no way in.","whys":["Level 1 is skill-based, his Q poke against your Void Shift blocking the opener.","Level 2 stays even as your shield timer negates his all-in threat.","Level 3 is even, decided by whether he can catch your shield down for a W engage.","Levels 4-5 remain skill-matched as you farm at range and he hunts a stun opening.","Level 6 favours Malzahar, whose point-click Nether Grasp suppresses his W all-in and cancels the combo.","First item favours Malzahar, whose ramping DPS outpaces a Pantheon whose damage is falling off.","With two-plus items Malzahar dominates, hard-countering his single-target dive with point-click R."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"qiyana","win":["Skill","Qiyana","Qiyana","Qiyana","Malzahar","Qiyana","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Qiyana's window, not yours. Once she has Q with an element she can walk up, poke, and all-in you before your E chunks her health, so hold Q for her engage and never step past your minions when her element is off cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R flips the lane. The moment Qiyana dashes in you suppress her, and even if she Zhonya-cancels the channel your Void Shift eats her follow-up. Save R purely as a self-peel answer to her all-in rather than an engage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After Rylai's or Zhonya's you can just R-point her and survive her combo, but her roams are the real threat now; if she shoves and vanishes, ping and match with your own push and cross-map E pressure."},{"when":"Late","text":"Suppression plus a defensive item makes you a reliable Qiyana-delete button in teamfights. Sit behind frontline, let her commit her Ult+Q wall, then R the diving Qiyana and let your team clean up."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach level 6 with health to spare","Farm safely with E and W voidlings","Save R and Zhonya for her all-in"],"foe":["Catch you with a river/brush element up","All-in you levels 2-5 before you spike","Roam after shoving the wave in"]},"early":"Level 1 is even because neither of you wants to commit, but from level 2 Qiyana owns the lane: with an element loaded her Q outranges and out-trades you, and she can flat kill you before your E is a threat. Give ground, last-hit at max range, and never contest her when her element is up.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay Qiyana-favoured since her all-in with element-empowered Q plus dash beats your immobile kit, so play for level 6. At 6 the lane inverts hard: your Nether Grasp point-blank suppresses her mid-combo and Void Shift blocks her opener, making her the one who has to respect you.","late":"With Rylai's or Zhonya's online you can bait her engage and R her out, but Qiyana's roam threat resurfaces at first item, so keep waves controlled and track her. By two items you are a dedicated Qiyana counter in fights, suppressing her the instant she dives your carries.","whys":["Neither champ wants to fight at level 1, so it comes down to pathing and pheromones—purely even.","With an element loaded Qiyana's empowered Q out-ranges your poke and she can trade freely.","At 3 her dash plus element all-in beats your immobile, pre-spike kit.","Levels 4-5 she still has kill pressure with element-Q while your E alone can't deter her.","Level 6 flips it—your point-blank R suppression and Void Shift shut her all-in down.","At first item her roam and re-engage threat re-emerge before your defensive item fully answers it.","By two items your suppression reliably deletes her when she dives, so fights favour you."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"ryze","win":["Malzahar","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Ryze","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ryze is a slow starter and so are you, but your E-into-W voidling package clears faster and pokes for free while his early Q costs a lot of mana. Shove with E, deny him relaxed farm, and punish any step-up with Q silence into E."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R answers his all-in cleanly. When Ryze roots you with E-Q and commits, either pop Void Shift on the root or R him through the trade—suppression cancels his combo and his lack of mobility means he can't disengage."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is Ryze's power spike: Archangel's/Tear stacked plus Rod means his Q chains hurt and his ult enables ganks. Respect his combo range, don't face-check his root, and farm from the back of the wave with E ticking."},{"when":"Late","text":"Two items in you outscale the fight—R locks the immobile Ryze and Void Shift blocks his root opener. Play to peel yourself and delete him whenever he flanks, since he has no dash to escape your grasp."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove with E and deny his farm","Bait his E root then R or shield it","Keep Void Shift up for his combo"],"foe":["Stack Tear/Archangel's uninterrupted","Land E-Q root to open a full combo","Use R to roam and snowball sidelanes"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours—Ryze is one of the weakest level-1 champs and your Q plus melee harass can win the first trade before either of you has waveclear. Through 2 and 3 it evens out as both of you are farming and neither wants to commit without cooldowns, so focus on last-hitting and shoving with E.","mid":"Levels 4-5 tilt back to you: your voidling shove and E chip keep him pinned while his mana-hungry Q makes aggressive trades costly for him. At 6 your Nether Grasp is a hard answer to his root-combo all-in, and with no mobility he can't punish you the way he'd like—this is why your win rate here is so high.","late":"Ryze's first-item Tear spike genuinely out-damages you for a window, so respect his Q chains and don't get rooted. Past two items you flip it back for good: suppression plus Void Shift neuters his combo, and you become the reliable answer to any Ryze flank or dive.","whys":["Ryze is a bottom-tier level-1 champ, so your Q and auto harass win the opening trade.","By level 2 both are farming with cooldowns down—an even, non-committal phase.","Level 3 stays even as neither has the tools to force a decisive fight yet.","Levels 4-5 your E shove and voidlings out-pressure his mana-hungry early Q.","Your level-6 R cleanly answers his root all-in and he can't escape it.","First-item Tear/Archangel's makes his Q chains spike and briefly out-damage you.","By two items your suppression and shield outscale him, evening then favouring the fight."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"swain","win":["Swain","Swain","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Swain's early is stronger—his W poke and E root let him zone you off the wave before your E is online. Don't walk up for cs when his E is up; a landed root plus W burst is a real chunk. Farm at range and wait out the phase."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R beats his all-in. When Swain E-roots and pops Demonic Ascension to sustain a fight, suppress him mid-drain—R cancels his ult value and Void Shift can eat the E root that starts it. This is where the lane turns your way."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You out-shove and out-trade him now: E spreads across his wave, W voidlings tank his Q, and you can R him whenever he steps up to drain. Keep the wave moving and threaten his roams with faster clear."},{"when":"Late","text":"Suppression shuts down the drain-tank fantasy. In fights let Swain W-pull and Ascend, then R the moment he's committed—he has no dash out, so your grasp plus team follow-up ends him."}],"wants":{"you":["Dodge his E root and farm at range","Reach 6 healthy, then R his drain","Out-shove with E and pressure roams"],"foe":["Zone you off cs with W poke","Land E root into W burst early","Sustain a long fight with Demonic Ascension"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 belong to Swain: his W deals meaningful poke and his E root threatens a burst combo while your kit is still just Q and a single E point. Respect his E range, take safe last-hits, and accept you'll concede a little cs rather than eat a root-into-W trade.","mid":"Level 3 onward evens as your E comes online and you can start shoving and spreading damage, blunting his zone control. At 6 the lane flips to you—your R suppresses him through Demonic Ascension so his drain-tank sustain never gets going, and Void Shift blunts the E root that would start his combo.","late":"First item cements your control: faster waveclear, voidlings that soak his Q, and an R that answers every step-up. Late game you're a clean counter to his frontline drain fantasy, suppressing him the instant he Ults, though a fed Swain flanking your backline is still a threat to track.","whys":["Level 1 Swain's W poke and E-root threat out-pressure your bare early kit.","At level 2 he still zones you off the wave with superior poke and root range.","Level 3 your E comes online and lets you shove back—the phase evens out.","Levels 4-5 stay even as your spread damage offsets his poke and root control.","Your level-6 R suppresses him through Demonic Ascension, shutting his sustain down.","First item you out-shove and can R every drain attempt, taking lane control.","Late fights are roughly even—your suppression counters his Ult but a fed Swain flank still threatens."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"sylas","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Skill matchup early—Sylas wants to E-dash in, chain his Q, and W-heal off you, but your Q silence interrupts his combo and E chip punishes him for lingering. Don't get greedy on trades where his W is up; poke with E and hold Q for his dash."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R is the entire lane. Sylas ults to steal an ult, but if he dives you your Nether Grasp suppresses him before he can cast, and Void Shift blocks his E stun chain. Save R strictly for when he commits and he simply loses the all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You spike hard here: R plus Rylai's/Zhonya's means any Sylas engage gets him suppressed and killed. Shove with E and W, deny his roams, and force him to fight into your point-and-click lockdown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Sylas stealing your R is worthless—it's a self-cast suppress that does little for him—so he'll take a teammate's instead. Peel yourself, let him dive, then R him out; he has the mobility to enter but not to escape your grasp."}],"wants":{"you":["Hold Q to interrupt his E dash-in","Save R for his level-6 all-in","Spike with Rylai's/Zhonya's and shove"],"foe":["Land E stun chain into full Q combo","W-heal off you during extended trades","Roam or dive with his ult mobility"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are a genuine skill matchup: Sylas has the dash, stun chain, and self-heal to make trades scary, but your Q silence can cut his combo short and your E punishes him for sitting in it. Play around his W cooldown—if it's down, his sustain isn't there—and don't over-extend where his double-E can catch you.","mid":"At 6 the lane swings to you. Sylas wants to all-in, but your R point-blank suppresses him before he lands his stun, and Void Shift eats the E that opens his combo. He can't reliably steal value from your ult either, so his 6 spike is far weaker into you than into most mids.","late":"First item locks in your edge—R plus a defensive item makes every Sylas engage a death sentence for him. Late game reverts to a skill fight: he has the mobility to flank your backline, so you must save R and Zhonya to answer his dive, but a clean grasp deletes him mid-combo.","whys":["Level 1 is even—your Q interrupt trades off against his dash-heal kit.","Level 2 stays skill-based as both look to punish mispositioning without full combos.","Level 3 his E stun chain is online but your Q silence answers it—still even.","Levels 4-5 remain a skill fight around his W-heal and your E poke timing.","Your level-6 R suppresses him before his stun lands, winning the all-in.","First item plus Rylai's/Zhonya's makes every Sylas engage suicidal—clearly yours.","Late fights even out since his ult mobility lets him flank if you waste R."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"syndra","win":["Skill","Skill","Syndra","Syndra","Malzahar","Syndra","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Syndra out-ranges and out-pokes you here—her Q-E stun and QW poke chip you down while you can't threaten her back. Don't stand in Q range for cs; use E from the back of the wave and accept last-hits under tower rather than eat free poke."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R answers her R. Syndra wants to combo-execute you, but your Nether Grasp suppresses her the instant she steps up, and Void Shift can block her E stun. Hold R purely as your all-in trump card—she can't burst you if she's suppressed."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Syndra spikes hard at Luden's/Rod: her sphere burst plus R can genuinely one-shot squishies, so respect her combo and don't get caught in the open. Farm safe, keep E ticking, and only trade when Void Shift is up."},{"when":"Late","text":"In fights you're her worst nightmare to engage onto—she has no escape, so R locks her down and cancels her ult. But if she catches you first with E-stun into R, you die, so play from Zhonya and let her waste her combo before you grasp."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 6 healthy and R her step-up","Farm from max E range under tower","Bait her E stun then Void Shift it"],"foe":["Poke you down with QW and Q-E stun","Land full combo into R execute","Control mid with sphere zoning"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are even as neither commits, but Syndra's superior range means you're already ceding a bit of poke. Focus on safe cs and don't give her free Q-E stun angles, because once she has her spheres up she starts to dictate the lane.","mid":"Levels 3-5 belong to Syndra: her poke and Q-E stun out-range everything you have, and she can zone you off cs while chipping you for a level-6 execute setup. Your job is to reach 6 with health, at which point your R flips one all-in—suppressing her before her combo lands—so the level-6 cell reads in your favour.","late":"First item is Syndra's spike, not yours—her burst can one-shot, so play respectful and farm from range. Late game evens out: you're the ideal engage-answer since she has no escape from your R, but she can equally delete you first if you're caught, so it comes down to who commits and whether your Void Shift and Zhonya are up.","whys":["Level 1 is even—neither has the tools to force a fight yet.","Level 2 stays even though Syndra's range starts to give her poke priority.","At level 3 her QW poke and Q-E stun out-range and out-trade you.","Levels 4-5 she zones you off cs and sets up a level-6 execute—clearly hers.","Your level-6 R suppresses her before her combo, winning the all-in.","First-item Luden's/Rod lets her one-shot squishies—her burst spike, not yours.","Late fights even out: you answer her engage but she can delete you if you're caught."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"taliyah","win":["Skill","Taliyah","Taliyah","Taliyah","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Taliyah out-pushes and out-pokes you here—her Q spam shoves waves instantly and chips you, and her E can zone you off cs. Don't try to match her push face-to-face; farm with E from range, respect her W knock-up when you're near walls, and watch for her level-6 roam."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R keeps you in lane while hers leaves it. Taliyah's ult is a roam tool, so ward and ping her missing—meanwhile your Nether Grasp answers any return gank and Void Shift blunts her W-Q burst. This is where lane priority shifts back to you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"You out-scale her lane bully phase now: E plus W voidlings match her push, and you can R her whenever she steps up to poke. Deny her roams by shoving first and cross-map E, and force her to fight into your lockdown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Taliyah's a poke-and-pick mage with a mobile ult but no reliable self-peel once you're on her. R locks her down in fights and Void Shift eats her W-Q engage, so sit safe, let her commit, then suppress and delete her."}],"wants":{"you":["Reach 6 and answer her roams","Match her push with E and voidlings","R her whenever she steps up to poke"],"foe":["Shove you in with Q and roam","Zone you off cs with E and poke","Land W-Q knockup burst early"]},"early":"Level 1 is even before her Q ramps, but from level 2 Taliyah takes over: her worked-ground Q shoves the wave and pokes you at once, and her E denies you comfortable cs. Play safe, last-hit with E, and don't get knocked into a wall by her W—concede a bit of lane rather than trade into her.","mid":"Levels 3-5 stay Taliyah-favoured as her push-and-poke keeps you pinned and sets up roams with her ult. The lane turns at 6: your R punishes any gank or step-up, Void Shift answers her W-Q, and your waveclear finally matches hers, so you stop bleeding priority.","late":"By first item you've flipped it—your E and voidlings out-sustain her push and your R answers every poke attempt. Two items in you're the clean counter to a mobile poke mage: she can't peel your suppression, so let her overcommit and grasp her out of the fight.","whys":["Level 1 is even before Taliyah's worked-ground Q ramps up.","At level 2 her Q shoves the wave and pokes you simultaneously—hers.","Level 3 her E zoning plus Q push keep you pinned off cs.","Levels 4-5 she controls priority and sets up ult roams—clearly hers.","Your level-6 R answers her roams and ganks, turning lane priority back to you.","First item your E and voidlings match her push and you R every step-up.","By two items your suppression cleanly counters her poke-and-pick kit."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"talon","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Talon","Talon","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Skill matchup early—Talon wants to W-Q all-in and roam, but your Q silence and E chip punish him if he lingers, and your voidlings soak his passive procs. Hold Q for his gap-close and don't let him get comfortable stacking his passive; every second he's in E range costs him health."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Talon's spike, not yours. With R plus Youmuu's timing his roam and dive potential peak, and his burst can outpace your R cast if he catches you first. Ward flanks, keep Void Shift up for his engage, and don't face-check—R is your only answer and it must land before he combos."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Still Talon-favoured on the map: Youmuu's turns him into a lane-to-lane assassin, so he'll roam even if you win the 1v1. Shove with E to deny his roam windows, ping his movements, and only R him when he actually commits onto you."},{"when":"Late","text":"The scaling flips to you—teamfights reward your point-and-click suppression over his single-target dive. Sit behind frontline, let Talon jump your backline, then R him mid-combo; Void Shift eats his opener and he has no way out of your grasp once you've peeled for yourself."}],"wants":{"you":["Hold Q to interrupt his W-Q dive","Shove with E to deny his roams","Save R and Zhonya for his all-in"],"foe":["Land W-Q passive-stack burst","Roam with R and Youmuu's for picks","Catch you before you can cast R"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are a skill fight: Talon's W-Q poke and passive stacking are dangerous, but your Q silence can interrupt his combo and your E makes him pay for extended trades. Play around his all-in windows—if his Q is down he can't burst you—and use voidlings to blunt his passive procs while you farm.","mid":"Levels 5-6 are Talon's power window. His ult plus first-item Youmuu's make him a roaming threat and give him the burst to potentially kill you before your R lands, so this is the phase you must survive: ward, keep Void Shift for his engage, and never get caught in the open. His map pressure is the real danger, not the straight 1v1.","late":"First item keeps him ahead on the map, so deny roams by shoving with E and tracking him. Late game the matchup flips to you: fights favour your suppression, and once you're peeling for yourself an over-committing Talon gets R'd mid-dive with no escape—which is why your two-item cell reads in your favour despite the sub-50 win rate.","whys":["Level 1 is even—your Q interrupt answers his early poke attempts.","Level 2 stays skill-based around his W-Q trade and your E punish.","Level 3 remains even as your silence can cut his combo short.","Levels 4-5 stay a skill fight around his all-in and roam timings.","Level 6 is Talon's spike—his R and burst can kill you before your grasp lands.","First-item Youmuu's makes him a roaming assassin who pressures the map—his phase.","Late fights favour your suppression, and an over-committing Talon dies to your R."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"twistedfate","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You out-shove him: E Malefic Visions into a minion plus W Void Swarm clears waves faster than his auto-and-Wildcards farm, so you dictate crash timing and deny him the free stacking window he wants."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R hard-suppresses a champion with almost no base durability; if he Gold-cards you first you still win the point-blank all-in because his kit has zero escape and your passive shield eats his Pick a Card burst."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Blackfire Torch or Rod online your E-W-Q chunk plus suppress simply deletes him in lane, and every time he leaves to Destiny-roam you take plates and crash the next wave into his tower."},{"when":"Late","text":"In fights your point-click R removes him from the teamfight instantly, and no card, Flash, or blue-card mana lets a stationary control mage survive being suppressed on top of your Voidlings."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove every wave with E-spread and W so he can never freely stack Gold cards or push for a roam window","Track his Destiny (level-6 ult) cooldown and ping his lane-leave so your team pre-rotates","Save R for the moment he steps up to last-hit, then suppress-and-Zhonya to guarantee the kill"],"foe":["Farm safely with autos and Wildcard from max range while stacking passive cards for a roam","Use Destiny to make plays on side lanes rather than duel you in lane","Poke you down with blue-card Wildcards so you can't commit your channel without dying first"]},"early":"The first four levels are a genuine skill matchup: neither of you threatens a clean solo kill, he farms with autos and Wildcard while you Q-poke and set up E on the wave. Respect that his Gold Card gives a point-blank stun, so don't walk into range with W on cooldown. Your job in this window is simply to shove faster than he can and bank a wave-state advantage for level 6.","mid":"From 6 onward the lane tilts to you. Your R suppresses a champion with no mobility and thin base stats, so any time he steps up to CS you can flash-suppress and kill through his Pick a Card. Keep the wave shoving so his only counterplay, Destiny, costs him farm to use; ping every roam and let your team punish the 4v5.","late":"With one item and beyond you own the matchup. Sustained E-W-Q plus a point-click ult means you win every extended trade, and in 5v5s your R deletes him from the fight before he can throw a single card, so play to catch him and force teamfights around your suppress.","whys":["Even lane at level 1 — both of you just farm and neither has kill pressure yet.","Still a skill matchup at 2; his Gold-card stun and your W trades cancel out.","Level 3 stays even as both complete the early kit and trade poke for waveclear.","Through 4-5 it remains a coinflip decided by wave state, not raw power.","At 6 you flip ahead — your suppress kills an escape-less mage that his ult can't save.","With first item your burst-plus-suppress out-damages him and punishes every roam attempt.","At 2+ items your point-click R removes him from every teamfight, so you stay favoured."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"veigar","win":["Malzahar","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You shove him in with E-W while he has no real waveclear until his Q refunds mana, so you deny his early Baleful Strike stacks and can crash-and-recall or set up a dive with your jungler."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your point-click R suppresses him before he can land Event Horizon, and your passive shield plus Voidlings blunt his Primordial Burst; walk up, suppress, Zhonya, and he dies without landing his cage combo."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With a first item you out-trade and out-push him; every time he steps to farm you threaten flash-suppress, and he cannot both stack AP safely and hold his E to peel you."},{"when":"Late","text":"This is where he wins the phase — infinite AP means his R executes you at low health and his Event Horizon stun locks your immobile body, so a fully-stacked Veigar can cage-and-delete you before your channel finishes."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove level 1-2 hard so he misses early Baleful Strike stacks and gives up CS or plates","All-in the instant your R is up while his Event Horizon is on cooldown","Buy Merc Treads and hold a QSS-line item so his cage can't chain into a guaranteed R execute later"],"foe":["Farm safely and last-hit minions with Q to stack permanent AP without trading","Land Event Horizon to root you, then W Dark Matter and R for a full point-blank burst","Reach late game where his infinite scaling and stun cage outrange and out-burst you"]},"early":"Level 1 is yours: he has no waveclear and can't contest a Q-plus-auto shove, so you push in and deny his first Baleful Strike stacks. Levels 2-3 settle into a skill lane as he gets Event Horizon online — respect that a landed cage means his full combo, so never walk into stun range with W and passive shield down. Keep the wave moving at him and make his farm awkward.","mid":"From level 4 through 6 you hold the edge. Your point-click suppress ignores his need to land a skillshot cage, and your shield plus Voidlings eat a chunk of his burst, so the level-6 all-in favours you if you force it before Event Horizon is up. This is your kill window — use it, because it closes as he stacks.","late":"The phase flips at two-plus items: Veigar's AP is unbounded, his R becomes a percent-health execute, and his cage reliably locks your stationary channel. A stacked Veigar can Event-Horizon-and-Primordial-Burst you out of the game, so late fights become a skill test of dodging his cage and holding QSS rather than a lane you simply win.","whys":["You win level 1 outright — he has no waveclear to answer your shove and stack denial.","Level 2 evens out as his cage comes online and both of you respect the trade.","Still even at 3 as he farms Q stacks safely and you can't force without risk.","Through 4-5 your point-click suppress beats his skillshot-reliant setup, so you edge ahead.","At 6 your all-in wins before he can land Event Horizon into his full combo.","With first item you out-push and threaten suppress on every step-up.","At 2+ items his infinite AP, execute R, and stun cage flip the matchup to him."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"vex","win":["Vex","Vex","Vex","Vex","Vex","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"She out-pokes you badly here: her Q Mistral Bolt and empowered Gloom auto chunk you every time you step to last-hit or lay E on the wave, and her E Looming Darkness fear interrupts your channel and your farm rhythm."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Even at 6 she has the edge — Shadow Surge is a long-range engage or execute, and while your R suppresses her, she can R-out or fear you before you complete the channel, so you can't freely commit into her Gloom poke."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is your turn: with Blackfire Torch or Rod your sustained E-W-Q plus suppress out-damages her mana-hungry poke, and your passive shield eats one Gloom proc so you can finally walk her down and R her before she surges away."},{"when":"Late","text":"It levels out — she remains an anti-mobility pick tool with global R pressure, but your point-click suppress is just as reliable a lockdown, so fights come down to who lands their engage first."}],"wants":{"you":["Farm at max range and soak minimal Gloom-empowered poke until your first item spikes","Bait her E fear before committing R so your channel isn't interrupted","Use your passive shield and Voidlings to tank one Q-auto proc, then all-in once she's low on mana"],"foe":["Poke you down every wave with Q and Gloom autos while you're forced to walk up for E","Hold E Looming Darkness to fear-cancel your R channel","Use Shadow Surge to pick you off or escape your suppress from range"]},"early":"Vex controls the early lane. Her Gloom passive punishes you every time you step up to place E on the wave or last-hit, and her Q out-ranges your Q Call of the Void, so you bleed health without much recourse. Do not try to force trades — your all-in relies on walking up, and her E fear plus poke make that suicidal before you have items. Farm patiently, take the poke on minions where you can, and survive to your first-item spike.","mid":"Through level 6 she keeps the advantage. Shadow Surge gives her both a long engage and an execute, and her fear reliably interrupts your suppress channel, so you can't answer her poke with a clean R commit. Play for scaling, ward against her roams, and only look for your ult when her E is down and your Voidlings and shield can absorb her burst.","late":"The matchup evens out at two-plus items. She stays a strong anti-assassin, anti-dive pick with global ult pressure, but your point-click R is an equally guaranteed lockdown that ignores her mobility. Fights hinge on who lands first: if you suppress her carry she's removed, and if she surges your team first she snowballs — so it becomes a skill matchup around engage timing.","whys":["Vex wins level 1 — her Gloom poke and range beat your step-up farming.","Still hers at 2 as she pokes freely and you can't trade back safely.","Level 3 favours her; her Q and fear out-range and interrupt your kit.","Through 4-5 she keeps poking you down while your all-in stays too risky.","At 6 she still edges it — Shadow Surge escapes or beats your channel commit.","With first item your sustained damage and shield flip the lane so you can walk her down.","At 2+ items it's even — your point-click suppress matches her pick-and-global pressure."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"viktor","win":["Viktor","Viktor","Viktor","Viktor","Malzahar","Malzahar","Viktor"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Viktor out-trades you here: his Q shield-and-empowered-auto wins short trades and his E Death Ray both waveclears with you and pokes you off your E-spread, so he contests the shove you normally dominate."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your window — your R point-click suppresses him before he can chain his Gravity Field into a combo, and your passive shield plus Voidlings blunt his Chaos Storm, so a level-6 all-in with Zhonya kills him."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item spike your suppress-plus-E-W-Q burst still beats him in a straight all-in, and you can punish him while his upgrade timings are awkward before he completes his core power spike."},{"when":"Late","text":"He takes the phase back: an upgraded E clears waves and out-ranges you, Gravity Field can stun-cancel your channel, and his Chaos Storm plus scaling let him kite and out-DPS your immobile body in every extended fight."}],"wants":{"you":["Survive the early poke and match his E waveclear so he can't freeze and zone you off farm","Force your all-in at 6 while his Gravity Field is down and your Voidlings are up","Buy Merc Treads and hold Zhonya so his stun zone can't lock your suppress channel late"],"foe":["Win short trades with Q shield and empowered autos, then poke with Death Ray","Upgrade E for waveclear so he pushes you in and roams or takes plates","Land Gravity Field to interrupt your R and out-scale you into a kiting hypercarry"]},"early":"Viktor holds the early edge. His Q gives him a shield and an empowered auto that wins the short trades you'd like to start, and his E Death Ray matches your waveclear while poking you off your E-spread, so you don't get the free shove this kit usually enjoys. Play safe, farm with W Voidlings, and don't step into his Q range with your shield down. The sub-50% win rate reflects that he simply out-lanes you if you play greedy.","mid":"Levels 5 and 6 are your window to swing it. Your point-click R suppresses him regardless of his Gravity Field, and your shield and Voidlings eat a chunk of his Chaos Storm burst, so if you all-in before his stun zone is available you win the fight. Use this spike aggressively, because it is the one clear moment the matchup belongs to you.","late":"The phase reverts to Viktor at two-plus items. His upgraded Death Ray out-ranges and out-clears you, Gravity Field reliably cancels your suppress channel, and his scaling turns him into a kiting hypercarry that out-DPSes your stationary self in extended fights. Late-game, hold Zhonya and QSS-type tools and look to catch him before he ramps, because a farmed Viktor beats you in a straight teamfight.","whys":["Viktor wins level 1 — his Q trade and range out-duel your step-up.","Still his at 2 as Q shield and empowered autos beat your short trades.","Level 3 favours him; Death Ray pokes and matches your waveclear.","Through 4-5 he keeps out-trading and zoning you off farm.","At 6 you flip it — suppress plus shield wins the all-in before his stun zone.","With first item your burst-and-suppress all-in still beats his awkward upgrade timing.","At 2+ items he retakes it — upgraded E, Gravity Field cancel, and scaling out-DPS you."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"vladimir","win":["Malzahar","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar","Skill"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You dominate the shove and the trades: E-W crashes waves while his early Transfusion sustain is on a long cooldown and costs health, so you push him under tower, deny CS, and threaten a jungler dive on your immobile-early opponent."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R suppresses him and, timed right, catches him with Sanguine Pool down so he can't W out of it; combined with your shield-and-Voidling all-in you delete him before Hemoplague matters."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With your first item your sustained E-W-Q plus suppress out-damages his sustain, and every recall he takes to heal is a wave you crash and a plate you collect — you stay firmly ahead."},{"when":"Late","text":"It levels off: Vladimir scales into a bruiser-mage teamfighter and his Sanguine Pool can cleanse your suppress if he pools the instant you channel, so late fights become a timing duel over your R versus his W."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove hard levels 1-5 to abuse his weak, health-costly early sustain and deny stacks","Bait or track his W Sanguine Pool before committing R so he can't cleanse the suppress","Punish every heal-recall by crashing the wave and taking plates or a roam"],"foe":["Farm safely with Q Transfusion and E poke, weathering your shove until he outscales","Use Sanguine Pool to dodge your R suppress and E Malefic Visions damage","Reach two items where his sustain, Hemoplague, and pool-cleanse turn fights even"]},"early":"Level 1 is clearly yours — you out-push and out-trade a Vladimir whose early Transfusion is weak, long-cooldown, and costs him health. Levels 2-3 read as skill only because he can play safe and farm with Q, but you still hold the shove and the initiative. Keep the wave crashing into him, deny his CS, and set up your jungler; his lane is a scaling survival act and you want to make the early game as painful as possible. The 55%+ win rate reflects how hard you can bully this window.","mid":"From 4 through 6 you keep the lead. Your point-click R suppresses him, and if you time it while his Sanguine Pool is on cooldown he simply dies to your shield-backed all-in before Hemoplague comes online. Every time he recalls to heal, punish it: crash the wave, take a plate, or roam. This is the stretch where you build the gold lead that decides the game.","late":"The matchup evens out at two-plus items. Vladimir scales into a durable teamfighter, his sustain lets him survive your poke, and a well-timed Sanguine Pool can cleanse your R mid-channel, negating your one guaranteed lockdown. Late-game becomes a timing duel — bait his W before you suppress, and rely on the lead you built early rather than expecting to win a farmed Vlad in a straight fight.","whys":["You win level 1 — your shove and trades crush his weak early sustain.","Level 2 reads even only because he can hunker down and farm safely.","Still even at 3 as he plays for scaling while you hold the initiative.","Through 4-5 you're ahead — you out-push and punish his health-costly heals.","At 6 your suppress plus shield kills him before Hemoplague, especially with his pool down.","With first item your sustained burst out-damages his sustain and you punish every recall.","At 2+ items it evens out — his scaling and pool-cleanse on your R level the fights."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"xerath","win":["Skill","Skill","Xerath","Xerath","Xerath","Xerath","Xerath"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once his kit is online he out-ranges everything you have: his Q Arcanopulse and W Eye of Destruction chunk you from screens away while you're forced to walk up to place E on the wave, so you bleed health with no way to trade back."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Shocking Orb plus his ultimate Rite of the Arcane give him long-range stun-and-artillery poke; you can't reach him to suppress, and stepping up to farm under his R barrage is where he wins the lane and assists ganks."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Manaflow and his first item his poke is relentless and cheap, so he keeps you permanently low and zoned off CS while threatening to help his jungler collect you from max range."},{"when":"Late","text":"He stays ahead — a farmed Xerath is pure artillery range, and your immobile self is the ideal target; you can only threaten him if you flank with Zhonya and a full E-W-Q-R suppress before he lands his stun."}],"wants":{"you":["Use W Voidlings and E to clear waves from a safer distance so you eat less Q poke","Buy early magic resist and a Rod for sustain, and hold Zhonya to survive his ult barrage","Look to flank or roam with your team since you can't win the direct poke war"],"foe":["Poke you from max range with Q and W while you walk up for farm","Land Shocking Orb E to set up his Q and jungle ganks","Zone you off CS and chip you with Rite of the Arcane from total safety"]},"early":"The first two levels are even — Xerath is clunky and mana-starved before his kit and Manaflow come online, so you can farm and trade Q pokes on roughly equal footing. Use this narrow window to hit your levels and shove, because it closes fast. Don't overstay once he has multiple ability ranks; the moment his range advantage kicks in, standing in lane just feeds him free poke.","mid":"From level 3 onward Xerath controls the lane through sheer range. His Q and W out-distance your entire kit, and you're forced to step into his poke every time you place E on the wave, so you take unanswered damage. At 6 his ultimate and Shocking Orb let him zone you off CS and set up ganks from safety — you cannot reach him to land your suppress. Play to clear with Voidlings, minimize the poke you eat, and don't int trying to force a fight you can't start.","late":"He keeps the advantage at two-plus items. A farmed Xerath is artillery incarnate, and your stationary channel makes you his dream target from max range. Your only real threat is a flank: Zhonya up, walk the fog, and land a full E-W-Q into R suppress before he can Shocking Orb you. Otherwise, farm side lanes safely, let your team engage past his poke, and rely on picks rather than a straight lane win.","whys":["Even at level 1 — Xerath is clunky and mana-starved before his kit comes online.","Still even at 2 as he can't yet fully leverage his range advantage.","At 3 he pulls ahead — his Q and W out-range your whole kit.","Through 4-5 he pokes you off CS from a distance you can't answer.","At 6 his ult and stun zone you from safety and set up ganks you can't contest.","With first item his cheap relentless poke keeps you low and zoned.","At 2+ items a farmed artillery Xerath keeps punishing your immobile body from max range."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"yasuo","win":["Skill","Yasuo","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Yasuo","Yasuo"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once he has E dash and Q he can flick onto you through the wave and windwall your Q Call of the Void; your answer is W Void Swarm and your passive shield, which absorb his burst and let you E-poke him back so most of this window is a skill trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is your spike — your R point-click suppresses him and completely ignores his mobility, so if you catch him without Wind Wall up you channel-and-Zhonya and he dies before he can knock up your team with his own ult."},{"when":"1st item","text":"He edges back here: with crit online and Wind Wall to block your Q setup, he can E-Q-flash around your suppress timing and burst you down if your Voidlings and shield aren't up to eat the all-in."},{"when":"Late","text":"A fed Yasuo with Wind Wall and mobility is dangerous into your immobile body — he can windwall the peel, dash through your Voidlings, and flash-dodge your channel, so late fights hinge on landing R before he reacts."}],"wants":{"you":["Keep W Voidlings and your passive shield up so they eat his E-Q all-in","Bait his Wind Wall before you commit, then R-suppress him with no mobility answer","Shove and roam — your waveclear lets you leave lane and punish his weak early roams"],"foe":["Use Wind Wall to block your Q and your ranged setup","Dash through the minion wave with E to close and burst you when your shield is down","Get crit and mobility online to flash-dodge your suppress channel"]},"early":"Level 1 is even, but he spikes at 2 with his second point — E dash plus Q lets him flick onto you and all-in before your kit is fully online, and Wind Wall shuts down your Q poke. Your saving grace is W Void Swarm and your passive shield: keep them up and they absorb his burst, turning levels 3-5 back into a skill matchup where you E-poke and shove while denying him a clean kill. Never fight with your shield and Voidlings down.","mid":"Level 6 is your moment. Your R is a point-click suppression that ignores every dash and dodge in his kit, so the instant you catch him without Wind Wall you can channel, Zhonya, and delete him before he lands his own knock-up ult. This is exactly why Malzahar is a comfortable Yasuo answer overall — force this window, and use your superior waveclear to shove and roam whenever he can't punish it.","late":"The later phases tilt back to him. With crit and mobility online he can windwall your setup, dash through your Voidlings, and flash to dodge your suppress channel, so a fed Yasuo becomes a real threat to your stationary body. Play around your R cooldown, hold your shield for his engage, and rely on team peel — if you land the suppress you win the fight, but if he baits it out you're vulnerable to his all-in.","whys":["Even at level 1 before either of you has a real all-in.","Yasuo spikes at 2 — E dash plus Q lets him flick on and burst you.","Level 3 evens out as your W Voidlings and shield absorb his all-in.","Through 4-5 it stays a skill trade — you poke and shove, he looks for dashes.","At 6 you win — your point-click suppress ignores his mobility and kills him.","With first item he edges back — crit and Wind Wall let him dodge your suppress timing.","At 2+ items a fed, mobile Yasuo can windwall and flash around your channel."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"yone","win":["Skill","Yone","Skill","Skill","Malzahar","Yone","Yone"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With E Malefic Visions online you shove the wave and zone Yone off the caster minions, but respect his Q3 knock-up window: once his Mortal Steel stacks to three he can gap-close and combo, so keep your passive Void Shift up before you step into last-hit range."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Nether Grasp is a hard answer to his all-in — when Yone commits E (Soul Unbound) and dashes in, R suppresses him mid-combo and voidlings shred him, and even if he ults out, his body has to return to its origin point where you can re-lock him."},{"when":"1st item","text":"After his first mythic Yone's E return-window plus R (Fate Sealed) knock-back lets him force repeated all-ins; you need Zhonya's timing and to hold Q Call of the Void as a silence-peel or you get bursted before suppression finishes."},{"when":"Late","text":"In teamfights a fed Yone flanks the backline and your single-target R only locks one of his dashes; group tight, use W voidlings as vision/peel and save passive plus Q silence for the moment he presses E."}],"wants":{"you":["Shove with E+W so Yone eats waves under tower and can't freeze for a favourable all-in","Keep Void Shift charged before every trade so his Q3 or R gets partially eaten","Hold R for the exact frame he commits E to lock him out of his own combo"],"foe":["Bait or wait out your passive spell shield, then Q3 knock-up into E all-in","Use E (Soul Unbound) to dash in and the return teleport to dodge your R","Scale to two items and flank your position so your point-click R only catches one dash"]},"early":"Level 1 is even scuttle for lane priority, but at Level 2 Yone's second point in Q plus Way of the Hunter momentum lets him win the first melee trade, so give ground and don't walk up without minions between you.","mid":"From 3 to 5 the lane neutralises — your E waveclear and shove deny him a freeze, and holding Void Shift blunts his engage — but at 6 you flip it hard: R Nether Grasp is a point-click suppress that answers his all-in and turns his dash-in into a free kill.","late":"Once Yone has his first item and stacked E return-windows his all-in threat outweighs your single lock; you're the safer scaler with waveclear and pick potential, but a fed Yone flanks around your one R, so play grouped and peel-first.","whys":["Level 1 is an even skill check with no abilities spiking either side and both just securing the wave.","At Level 2 Yone's early melee power and Q momentum let him win the first extended trade, favouring him.","By Level 3 your E waveclear and Void Shift passive even out his engage, making it a skill matchup.","Through Levels 4-5 you shove and he can't freeze, so the lane stays even and comes down to spell-shield timing.","At Level 6 your R suppresses his all-in and locks his E dash, giving you the clear kill threat.","With one item Yone's stacked E return-windows and knock-back let him force all-ins faster than your R recovers, favouring him.","With two-plus items a fed Yone flanks past your single-target lock and outputs more in fights, favouring him."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"zed","win":["Skill","Skill","Zed","Zed","Malzahar","Zed","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Zed's poke window: he pushes with Q (Razor Shuriken) through the wave and shadow-doubles it, so keep Void Shift charged since your passive spell shield eats a full Q and denies his energy-efficient poke, then punish his low mana with E harass."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Nether Grasp is the reason this matchup swings your way — when Zed ults (Death Mark) and appears on you, R point-click suppresses him so he can't reposition or auto-weave, and your passive can pre-eat his mark's projected damage; hold R for his all-in, don't waste it clearing."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With Duskblade/Ludens online Zed's R burst can kill you before suppression pays off if your passive is down, so track your Void Shift cooldown, buy Zhonya's early, and only step up when both your shield and R are available."},{"when":"Late","text":"Post-Zhonya you fully counter his engage: bait the R, eat the mark with your stopwatch or spell shield, then R him as it expires; grouped, your voidlings and E waveclear keep you safe while he struggles to find a clean pick on you."}],"wants":{"you":["Keep Void Shift up so his Q poke and Death Mark projection are eaten by your spell shield","Hold R exclusively for the moment he ults onto you","Rush Zhonya's so his all-in window becomes your kill window"],"foe":["Poke you down with double-Q shadow harass while your passive is on cooldown","All-in with R when your Void Shift and Nether Grasp are both unavailable","Roam with W+W shadow mobility to snowball side lanes off your immobility"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even skill check — Zed can't all-in yet and you're just securing farm — so focus on not eating free Q pokes and keep the wave central.","mid":"From 3 to 5 Zed spikes: his shadow-Q poke and roam threat pressure you, and your passive can only block so much, so play safe and shove with E rather than dueling; the moment you hit 6 the lane flips, because R suppression plus spell shield hard-answers his Death Mark all-in.","late":"With one item Zed's burst can still race your suppression if you're careless, but with two-plus items and a Zhonya's you cleanly counter him — bait the ult, survive it, then lock him as the mark pops, which is why the overall matchup favours you.","whys":["Level 1 neither champion has a kill threat, so it's an even skill start.","Level 2 stays even — Zed lacks his shadow combo power spike and you both just farm.","At Level 3 Zed's double-Q shadow poke and energy sustain let him win the harass war, favouring him.","Through Levels 4-5 his roam pressure and poke keep him ahead while you lack your ultimate answer.","At Level 6 your R suppression and spell-shield passive hard-counter his Death Mark all-in, favouring you.","With one item Zed's lethality burst can still outrace your suppression when your passive is down, favouring him.","With two-plus items and Zhonya's you fully counter his engage and win the extended fight, favouring you."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"ziggs","win":["Skill","Skill","Ziggs","Ziggs","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Ziggs out-ranges you and pokes with Q (Bouncing Bomb) plus W (Satchel Charge) to zone you off the wave; your passive Void Shift can eat one bomb but not sustained artillery, so use E Malefic Visions to match his push and avoid extended standing in his Q bounce lines."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Nether Grasp gives you the pick tool he lacks — Ziggs is immobile except for his W self-knockback, so if you can flash-R or catch him stepping up, you suppress and delete him, whereas his R (Mega Inferno Bomb) is waveclear/poke, not a duel answer."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With E+W pushing you match his waveclear and start roaming; Ziggs is stuck shoving and can't follow, so use your superior R-pick threat and voidling DPS to punish his lane-bound artillery playstyle on the map."},{"when":"Late","text":"Teamfights favour your engage — Ziggs wants to sit back and chunk, but your R locks a carry and voidlings apply constant pressure; the lane itself is a coinflip on poke, so your edge comes from picks and objective setups, not the 1v1."}],"wants":{"you":["Match his push with E+W so he can't freeze you out of farm","Land a flash-R or catch his step-up since he has almost no escape","Use your roam and pick threat to punish his lane-locked artillery"],"foe":["Poke you under tower with long-range Q bombs and W zoning","Use W Satchel Charge self-knockback to dodge your R engage","Sit back in fights and chunk your team from max range"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even, farm-focused start — Ziggs can chip you with Q but has no all-in, so just secure creeps and keep the wave from freezing on his side.","mid":"From 3 to 5 Ziggs' artillery range lets him poke and zone you, edging the lane in his favour; play for farm with E, hold your passive for his bombs, and don't over-extend into his W knockback traps.","late":"At 6 and into items the matchup levels and tips your way — your R gives you the pick potential he can't answer, your waveclear frees you to roam, and grouped your suppression plus voidlings outvalue his stationary poke, which matches the coinflip win rate resolving on your engage.","whys":["Level 1 is an even farming start with neither champion holding a kill threat.","Level 2 stays even — Ziggs pokes but can't commit, and you both prioritise the wave.","At Level 3 Ziggs' longer range and Q bomb poke let him zone you off farm, favouring him.","Through Levels 4-5 his artillery poke and W zoning keep the lane pressure on his side.","At Level 6 your R suppression gives you a pick tool the immobile Ziggs can't answer, favouring you.","With one item your E+W waveclear matches his push and frees you to roam, favouring you.","With two-plus items your engage and voidling DPS outvalue his stationary poke in fights, favouring you."]},
  {"a":"malzahar_mid","b":"zoe","win":["Skill","Skill","Zoe","Zoe","Malzahar","Malzahar","Malzahar"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"This is Zoe's danger window: she wants to land E (Sleepy Trouble Bubble) then follow with a charged Q (Paddle Star) for one-shot damage, so keep Void Shift charged — your passive spell shield eats the sleep bubble and denies her entire combo, and side-step the bubble along minion lines when your shield is down."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your R Nether Grasp answers the mobility her Q1 blink and W item-dashes give her — if she steps up to poke, flash-R or R her mid-animation suppresses through her escape, while her ult is a repositioning tool, not a duel answer, so 6 flips the lane firmly to you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"With E+W you shove her in and roam; Zoe is lane-bound and squishy, and your pick threat plus voidling DPS punish her whenever she overextends for a poke, so use your waveclear tempo to snowball the map around her."},{"when":"Late","text":"In fights your engage beats her poke — she has to land a skillshot bubble from range while your voidlings and R lock a target; hold your passive for her E and she loses her only pick tool, letting you walk her down in the mid-late game."}],"wants":{"you":["Keep Void Shift up so your spell shield eats her E sleep bubble and kills her combo","Side-step the bubble along minion lines when your passive is on cooldown","Use flash-R or a step-up R to suppress through her Q blink and item dashes"],"foe":["Land E Sleepy Trouble Bubble then charged Q for a one-shot while your passive is down","Poke with long-range Q and pick up Spell Thief bubbles to burst you","Use Q1 blink and W dashes to dodge your R and stay at max range"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are an even farming start — Zoe can chip with Q but her combo isn't online, so secure creeps and hold Void Shift ready for her first bubble attempt.","mid":"From 3 to 5 Zoe is at her most dangerous: her E-into-Q one-shot can delete you if you get slept, so play respectfully, keep your spell shield charged to eat the bubble, and shove with E rather than dueling in her poke range.","late":"At 6 and beyond the matchup swings hard to you — R suppression answers her mobility, your spell shield hard-counters her one combo, and your waveclear-plus-roam tempo lets you snowball the map, which is exactly why the win rate is so strongly in your favour.","whys":["Level 1 is an even farm start with neither champion able to commit a kill.","Level 2 stays even — Zoe pokes with Q but her sleep combo isn't online yet.","At Level 3 Zoe's E-into-Q one-shot threat lets her win the lane on a single landed bubble, favouring her.","Through Levels 4-5 her burst combo and long-range poke keep the pressure on her side.","At Level 6 your R suppression and spell-shield passive hard-counter her mobility and her only combo, favouring you.","With one item your E+W waveclear shoves her in and frees your roam against a lane-bound Zoe, favouring you.","With two-plus items your engage and voidling DPS overwhelm her single-pick poke in fights, favouring you."]}
